Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.10,0:00:07.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,有一个问题是：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: One question:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.20,0:00:11.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么会有那么丰富的物种？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why is there such a stunning diversity of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.21,0:00:15.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,答案是：进化论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One answer: Evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.21,0:00:18.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,查尔斯·达尔文的伟大发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charles Darwin's  brilliant theory
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.15,0:00:22.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,阐述了各物种如何适应自然和进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that explains how species adapt end change.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:27.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,它被人们称颂为最伟大的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been called the best idea anyone ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.22,0:00:31.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,但还有一个大问题：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's one big problem:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.03,0:00:34.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,进化论实际上是如何影响生物进化的过程的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How does it actually work?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:40.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在，卓越的科学为你解答这一问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now,extraordinary science is answering that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:45.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,揭开这个隐藏机制的神秘面纱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is uncovering the hidden mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.07,0:00:46.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,从生物体内开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inside creatures' bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.28,0:00:50.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,它可以解释这些惊人的演变过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can explain astonishing transformations,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.25,0:00:54.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像一些恐龙进化成了现在的鸟类...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like how birds can evolve from dinosaurs...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.02,0:00:59.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么鱼类曾经是你的祖先...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why a fish was once your ancestor...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.02,0:01:02.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及最重要的，究竟是什么造就了我们人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and,above all,what makes us human.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.26,0:01:07.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在，在NOVA节目中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right new on NOVA,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.06,0:01:11.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,你会发现一些连达尔文也不知道的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll find out what Darwin never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.18,0:01:28.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,NOVA主要由如下企业赞助：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Major funding for NOVA is provided by the following:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.05,0:01:30.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,埃克森美孚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ExxonMobil,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.22,0:01:34.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,承担世界上最艰难的能源挑战\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taking on the world's toughest energy challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.09,0:01:39.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时感谢戴维·科赫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And by David H.Koch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:44.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.31,0:01:53.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,公共广播公司\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And by the Corporation for Public Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.31,0:01:57.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及以下给PBS的特别赞助\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and by contributions to your PBS station from:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.28,0:02:05.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,普洛麦格集团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Additional funding by Promega Corporation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.39,0:02:07.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,天天新发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}discovering every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.26,0:02:11.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,普洛麦格，生命的科学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Promega,the science of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.23,0:02:14.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时感谢威斯康辛校友研究基金会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And by the Wisconsin Alumni Research Foundation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.16,0:02:18.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,给予威斯康辛大学的鼎力支持\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in support of the University of Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:26.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,在地球上，生命之树有着惊人丰富的种类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The Tree of Life on earth is one of stunning diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.35,0:02:40.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,9000多种鸟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}9.000 species of birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:46.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,350000种昆虫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}350,000 kinds of beetles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.17,0:02:54.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,28000种鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}28,000 types of fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.34,0:02:59.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,总共有两百万种生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Two million living species and counting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.21,0:03:07.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,而我们，只是其中的一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we are just one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:16.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,（鸟鸣声）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(birds calling)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:22.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是为什么动物种类繁多？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But why is there such an amazing variety of animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.30,0:03:30.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么鱼的种类琳琅满目？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why are there so many types of fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:35.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么昆虫又千奇百怪？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So many different species of beetle?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:39.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,这么多不同的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did this extraordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:41.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,是怎么产生的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}profusion of life on earth come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:44.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,今天，我们非常高兴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today,we celebrate the man
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.45,0:03:48.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们可以解决这些问题了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who would ultimately answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:53.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,查尔斯·达尔文\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charles Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.43,0:03:56.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,他出生于两百年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was born 200 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.20,0:03:59.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,150年前，他发表了他的巨作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it is 150 years since he published the work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.43,0:04:01.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,那是我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has become the bedrock
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.40,0:04:05.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究地球上生物的里程碑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our understanding of life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.44,0:04:07.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾：达尔文所想弄明白的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CLIFF TABIN: What Darwin wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:08.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,是地球为什么有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to understand was how you get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:11.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,如此丰富的物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this eotraordinary diversity of life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.35,0:04:13.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,他完全正确.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was spot on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.32,0:04:16.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,他真的成功了.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He really nailed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.35,0:04:19.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文的理论革命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Darwin's theory of evolution--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.29,0:04:22.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,他的理论解释了各个物种是如何进化的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}his account of why species adapt and change--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.39,0:04:26.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,被称为最完美的理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been called the best idea anyone ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.36,0:04:30.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,但达尔文承认：他的工作还没有完善\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even Darwin admitted that his work was incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.47,0:04:36.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,很多问题还是不能回答\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vast questions ware still unanswered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:38.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么，最大的问题是：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the biggest question was: How?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:40.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个巨大的变革是怎样在地球开始的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did evolution take place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.28,0:04:44.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔: 他不知道到底是什么动力促使这些变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SEAN CARROLL: He didn't know any of the mechanics of that process.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.35,0:04:48.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,他不明白这些物质的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he didn't understand the physical forces
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.28,0:04:52.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,改变了生物进化的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would actually change the way species appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:55.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是，在今天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But today,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.49,0:04:59.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以解答这些达尔文不知道的问题了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can answer the questions that Darwin could not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:09.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以看清进化的本质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can look under the hood of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.47,0:05:13.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,清楚神奇的进化过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and see exactly how this mysterious process
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.34,0:05:16.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,是如何使得物种千变万化的.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gives rise to such astounding diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:19.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾: 从科学的角度来讲，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}TABIN:What's incredible about this time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:20.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,最让我们难以置信的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a scientific perspective is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.52,0:05:23.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们逐渐可以理解自然界的物种多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're going to be able to understand that diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.39,0:05:26.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使我们十分兴奋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that just adds to the excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:27.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,它不再笼罩着神秘的面纱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't demystify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.49,0:05:30.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,它使这一切更神奇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It makes it all the more magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:34.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,这---就是神秘的进化论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR:And this is the magic and mystery of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:38.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个单一的物种，经过亿万年的演变，衍生出众多物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over eons of time,a single species gives rise to many.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.34,0:05:43.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,古老的鱼成为了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An ancient fish evolves to become the ancestor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.51,0:05:47.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,爬行动物的祖先，甚至包括我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of all four-limbed animals,even us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.34,0:05:51.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类，这一种生物，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one species,our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:53.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,逐渐产生了独一无二而又复杂的大脑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}develops e large and uniquely complex brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:57.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,使得我们主宰了这个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}enabling us to dominate the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.39,0:06:00.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个研究回答了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the search for the answers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.39,0:06:04.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文一直都不明白的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to what Darwin never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:09.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,（儿童交谈声）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(children chattering)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:13.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文从小就对自然有独特的情感\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin began his love affair with nature when ha was a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:17.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,和现在很多他的追随者一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}jest like many of his modern followers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.54,0:06:21.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,包括进化论和生物学家，肖恩·卡罗尔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including evolutionary biologist,Sean Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:26.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：我培养我对动物的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: I developed my interest in animals the same way I think
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:28.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,和很多生物学家一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most biologists did,which was either
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.35,0:06:30.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,一般去后院园子或者去动物园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}going out in the backyard or going to zoos.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.39,0:06:34.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,一旦有机会出现，我会立刻抓住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And anytime I got a chance,I'd flip over logs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.42,0:06:35.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,去寻找蝾螈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and look for salamanders
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.56,0:06:37.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,蛇，青蛙等等这些小动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and snakes and frogs and things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:40.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,我对它们的行为着迷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I was just fascinated with their patterns and behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.40,0:06:44.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,年轻的查尔斯·达尔文亦是如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR:So it was with the young Charles Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.60,0:06:48.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：年轻的查尔斯喜欢在野外溜达\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARRALL:Young Charles liked to traipse around the outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.40,0:06:50.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,他喜欢收集各种昆虫等东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He loved to collect beetles and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.37,0:06:51.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,他完全就是普通的孩子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was a completeld ordinary kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:54.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,不喜欢学校\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he didn't like school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:57.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,事实上，达尔文这可怜的学生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact,he was such a poor student that his father,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:01.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,连他爸爸，这成功而又仪表堂堂的医生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a rather successful physician and a pretty imposing figure,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:04.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,都对达尔文的人生之路十分忧心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was worried about Darwin's direction in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:08.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以他父亲把他送到了爱丁堡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So his father packed him off to Edinburgh,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:12.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,最有名的医学院，想他成为一个医生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the finest medical school in Europe,to become a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:21.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,但年轻的达尔文太过于拘谨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But young Charles was just too squeamish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.47,0:07:24.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：他被这个医学院深深震惊了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CCRROLL: And he was really horrified by medical school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:27.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,他亲眼目睹了一次儿童手术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He witnessed an operation on a child
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:28.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且是在没有麻醉的情况下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is in the era before anesthetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:32.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,他逃离了手术室并发誓不再回去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he just fled the operating theater vowing never to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.69,0:07:43.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,接着，他父亲把他送到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR:Next,his father sent him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.39,0:07:47.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,剑桥大学去学做一个牧师\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to Cambridge to study for the clergy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:50.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文还是没有坚持下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He didn't succeed at that either,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.67,0:07:53.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是他却找到了他的人生方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but he did find his direction in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.67,0:07:56.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,恢复了他孩童时代对自然的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reviving his childhood interest in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.44,0:08:00.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文开始了他在生物多样性方面的研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Darwin starts on his path to his divinity degree
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:03.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,作为一个学生，他慢慢地成熟了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anh he starts to mature as a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.51,0:08:04.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,他对某些科目更加的认真对待\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He becomes more serious about some subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.61,0:08:08.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,特别是自然历史学，并且学到了很多关于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}particularly natural history,and he learns a lot more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:10.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,植物学和地理学方面的知识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about botany and about geology and these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.52,0:08:13.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,他成为了一个出色的科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he's becoming a pretty solid field scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:16.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,作为一个自然学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: His reputation as a naturalist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.73,0:08:20.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,他获得巨大的荣誉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gained him a spectacular invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:21.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文被派遣到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Charles was offered a place
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.53,0:08:23.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,一艘英国海军军舰——贝格尔号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the British Navy ship the HMS Beagle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.67,0:08:27.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,那艘军舰平时负责南美洲的巡航\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whose mission was to survey the waters around South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.51,0:08:33.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,贝格尔号的船长想找一个饱读诗书的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now,the captain of the Beagle wanted a well-educated,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.71,0:08:36.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,懂科学 可以一起聚餐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientific person aboard,and a dinner companion,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.61,0:08:38.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,一起谈天说地的伙伴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}somodody to share conversation with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.58,0:08:42.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文就完全符合这些要求\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Darwin fit the bill perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.52,0:08:52.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,就这样 达尔文踏上了改变他一生的旅途\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And so,Charles Darwin set off on a fateful voyage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:56.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,它使我们对大自然多样性的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would revolutionize our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:09:00.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,有了翻天覆地的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of life's great diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:05.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文在贝格尔号上的旅途差不多有5年之久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The voyage of the Beagle took nearly five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.61,0:09:09.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,从佛得角群岛出发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wove its way from the Cape Verde islands
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:12.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,沿着巴西的海岸线一直走\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and along the coast of Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.61,0:09:14.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,当到了阿根廷的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was in Argentina that ha made
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:18.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文有了第一个重要的研究发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}his first important discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.69,0:09:20.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：在旅途的早些时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL:Early on in the voyage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:21.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文发现了一些让人惊讶的化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin found some amazing fossils.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.76,0:09:25.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,他挖出一些巨型哺乳动物的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He dug up some skulls,sown jaws,some backbones
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.69,0:09:28.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,头骨、颚、脊骨等等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what turned out to be giant mammals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:32.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些生物显然已经灭绝，而达尔文开始思考\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now,these were clearly extinct and Darwin began to ponder,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.54,0:09:35.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些化石和现在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what was the relationship of those fossils
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:39.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,生活在南美洲的动物有什么联系呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the living animals of South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:48.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文行进中，来到一个停靠港，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But one port of call on Darwin's voyage
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.55,0:09:52.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个港口，将会证明是最重要的那个.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}proved more important than all the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,它，就是加拉帕戈斯群岛.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Galapagos.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:10:01.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,此岛由13个孤立小岛组成的群岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This cluster of 13 isolated islands
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.80,0:10:05.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,在离厄瓜多尔600英里的太平洋中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lies 600 miles off the coast of Ecuador in the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.77,0:10:09.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,这里是很多不寻常动物的乐园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These islands are home to unusual animals
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.67,0:10:14.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,在地球其他地方都看不到这样的景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}found nowhere else on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.81,0:10:18.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,企鹅竟然生活在赤道上 在暖水里游泳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Penguins that live at the equator and swim in warm water,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:22.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,而不是在南极冰冷的海水当中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}instead of the frigid seas of the South Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.62,0:10:27.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,巨龟有600英镑重\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Giant tortoises that weigh up to 600 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:32.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,绿鬣蜥 巨型的蜥蜴在海水里游泳和潜水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Iguanas,huge lizards that swim and dive in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:38.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同于其它地方 他们只住在岛上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everywhere else,they dwell only on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:43.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,（狗叫声）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(barking)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.77,0:10:46.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,第一次去加拉帕戈斯群岛时，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Traveling for the first time in the Galapagos,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:49.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,肖恩·卡罗尔看到使达尔文异常好奇的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sean Carroll is seeing the same creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:51.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,同样景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that so intrigued Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:54.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：在所有的动物当中 我觉得海洋鬣蜥\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Of all animals,I think these marine iguanas
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.75,0:10:56.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,是加拉帕戈斯最具代表性的象征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the greatest symbol of the Galagagos,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.68,0:10:57.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,也是我在这里最想看到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what I most wanted to see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:10:59.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,希望观察他们的生活习惯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to see them in their native habitat,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.69,0:11:00.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,和那黑岩浑然一体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}blending against that black rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:02.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像达尔文描述的那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just as Darwin described it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.82,0:11:05.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,这让人无比的激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's an absolute thrill.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.86,0:11:09.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个面目狰狞的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DARWIN(dramatized):It's a hideous looking creature,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:12.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,脏脏的黑色的外表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a dirty black color,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.57,0:11:16.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,移动起来笨拙、呆滞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stupid and sluggish in its movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.77,0:11:20.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们的外表和土地一样黑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're as black as the porous rocks over which they crawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:26.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文在他的日志里描述了绿鬣蜥\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRTTOR: Derwic meticulously described the iguanas in his diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:31.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,但那时，他还与日后将成为的科学权威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he was far from the scientific authority
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:33.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,相距甚远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he would become.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.72,0:11:36.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：那时的达尔文\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: The Darwin that arrived here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.62,0:11:38.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,并不是我现在说的伟大的理论家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was not the great theorist that we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:41.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,他只是一个26岁的收藏家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was a 26-year-old collector,collecting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.60,0:11:43.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,几乎是随机的收藏各种植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really,almost at randow,any kind of plants,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.77,0:11:45.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,各种动物和各种石头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any kind of animals,any kinds of rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.73,0:11:46.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,他甚至不知道他收藏的这些东西有什么意义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He didn't even know the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.73,0:11:50.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,知道后来才被发现它的价值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what he was collecting until much later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.74,0:11:54.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,他也对巨龟非常着迷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: He was also tascinated by the giant tortoises,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.71,0:11:56.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些巨龟甚至允许他骑在它们的背上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which allowed him to ride on their backs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:11:59.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,慢慢的在地上挪动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as they slowly lumbered around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:02.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文：我经常爬到它们的背上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DARWIN: I frequently got on their backs
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:06.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,坐在它们的外壳上说唱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then,upon giving a few raps on the hinder part of the shell,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:09.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们就会起身爬走\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they would rise up and walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:13.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是我这时会很难保持身体的平衡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But I found it very difficult to keep my balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.86,0:12:17.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文测试这些生物到底缓慢到什么地步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Darwin measured the creatures' extreme slowness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:22.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,他算了一下，一天才爬4英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About four miles a day,he calculated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.64,0:12:24.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是当地人知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the local people knew
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:26.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,关于这些乌龟的其他事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something else about the tortoises.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.71,0:12:29.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们可以仅凭看他们的龟壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(whispering): They could tell which island any tortoise came from
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.74,0:12:32.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,说出这些龟是来自哪个小岛的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}jest by looking at its shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:34.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们的龟壳根据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Their shells differed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:38.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们居住的小岛的环境而不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depending on which island they lived on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.69,0:12:45.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些龟的壳塑造成一个拱顶的形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some tortoises had shells shaped like a dome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.69,0:12:50.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些则有一道飞弧在头上，就像一个鞍状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others had shells arcing over their heeds like a saddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.77,0:13:01.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些就是颜色略有差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others differed subtly in color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.91,0:13:05.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,或者可以从龟壳的底部看出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or by how much thu bottom of the shell flared out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.95,0:13:10.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文已经慢慢找到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin had literally been sitting on a clue--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.69,0:13:14.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,理解生物多样性途径的线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a way to understand the great diversity of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.79,0:13:18.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,但他还是没有意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but he didn't yet realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:25.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,（鸟鸣声）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(birds calling)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.83,0:13:29.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,相反，达尔文把他的注意力移到了鸟类身上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead,Darwin turned his attention to birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.94,0:13:33.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些小岛上遍地都是各种貌似是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The islands were full of what seemed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.94,0:13:37.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,相似物种的种群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a familiar assortment of species.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.85,0:13:43.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以，他拿起袋子收集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,he stuffed his collecting bag
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:46.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,他认为属于雀类的鸟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with what he thought were types of finches,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.89,0:13:50.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,锡嘴雀、鹪鹩和画眉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}grosbeaks,wrens and blackbirds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:54.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,五周之后，在加拉帕戈斯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then,after five weeks in the Galapagos,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:58.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文去了太平洋其他的港口\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin and the Beagle went to other ports in the Pacific
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.83,0:14:02.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,进行回家前的最后一次航行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and finally set sail for home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.84,0:14:05.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,回到了陆地，他开始整理他在旅途中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On board,ha started to sort through
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:08.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,在这整整五年时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the vast number of specimens he had collected
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.98,0:14:12.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,收集的大量物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the five-year voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:20.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是一直到他回到英国\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was not until he returned to Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:22.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,才能发现它们的价值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that ha was able to make sense of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.76,0:14:26.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,它开启了一个翻天覆地的变革\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It began with a starting revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.79,0:14:28.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文收集的各种鸟类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the different birds he had collected
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.83,0:14:32.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,其实由一种变异衍变而来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually were variations of a single type.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.84,0:14:38.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文留意到，他在加拉帕戈斯收集了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: He learns that those birds he had collected on the Galapagos
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.77,0:14:43.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,代表了13种雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually represent 13 different species of finch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.91,0:14:49.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而，这些鸟长得差异很大却使达尔文困惑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: What misled Darwin was that they looked radically different.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:53.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些鸟有宽而强硬的喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some had wide,tough beaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:54.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些的喙却有长又细\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others had long slender ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.89,0:14:58.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这些不同的特征和它们居住的小岛有着密切关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these differences depended on which islands they lived on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.09,0:15:00.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：为什么会这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Now,why would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:02.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不同种类的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why would there be slightly different birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.93,0:15:06.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同种群的小鸟分布在不同的小岛上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slightly different species on different islands
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.93,0:15:09.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这都发生在这个世界上的同一小角落？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all in one part of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:13.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文回想起加拉帕戈斯的海龟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Darwin now thought back to the Galapagos tortoises.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.98,0:15:17.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同海岛上的海龟差异非常大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They too differed from island to island.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:26.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,他觉得慢慢明白了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His brain began racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.12,0:15:28.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：想法慢慢成为思想了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Thoughts are starting to crystallize,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:31.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,在他脑海里一点一点地慢慢凝聚起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}take shape in his mind,bit by bit,bit by bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,他描述这个过程为精神震撼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He starts this process he describes as mental rioting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:37.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,在浩瀚的思绪中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just stream of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.10,0:15:39.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,他一点一点的记录那些头绪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where he's jotting down note after note after note.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.87,0:15:40.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,思想自动浮现在他脑海中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thoughts as they occur to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.97,0:15:44.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,最后 他把所有思想总结成一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And finally,they converge on this one idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:48.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文现在意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: What Darwin now realized
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.84,0:15:52.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为某些原因，各个物种发生了某种变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was that somehow,for some reason,species change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:04.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,在之前，它们肯定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Originally,there must have been
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:06.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,同属于加拉帕戈斯群岛的一个物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just one type of finch in the Galapagos,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:10.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过，随着时间的推移，这个物种衍变分化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but over time it had diversified
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:13.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,产生了长着各种喙的种群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into many kinds,with different beak shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.14,0:16:17.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,海龟的衍变也是同样的道理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same for the tortoises.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.97,0:16:21.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个海龟种群经过衍变产生了众多不同的种群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One type of tortoise must have turned into many kinds,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:25.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为居住的小岛的环境不同，它们长出了不同的龟壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with different shells depending on which island they lived on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:34.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,带着这个深刻的理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With this great insight,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:38.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文走进了新的危险的境地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin entering dangerous new territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:39.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,那个时代的标准观念是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The standard view at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:41.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,上帝创造了各个物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was that God had created every species.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:45.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,上帝做的就是最好的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that what God had created was perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.03,0:16:47.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,不容许丝毫改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.13,0:16:49.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：但是达尔文敢说不\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: But Darwin said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.87,0:16:52.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么造物主会不厌其烦地造出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why would the Creator bother with making
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.94,0:16:53.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,有细小差别的鸟雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slightly different finches
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.91,0:16:55.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,分布在不同而又无多大差别的小岛上？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for each of these different islands that all looked alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:59.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,当时流行的观点无法解释这一个问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRTTOR: The prevailing view just didn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.15,0:17:09.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,但这仅是达尔文革命的开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this was only the beginning of Darwin's revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:13.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,他把注意力转移到了化石上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He turned his attention to the fossils
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:16.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,化石是从南美洲收集起来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he had collected in South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.96,0:17:20.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一个是巨型的树懒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One was of a giant sloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.94,0:17:25.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外一个是巨大的犰狳样的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another was of a huge armadillo-like creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:30.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些动物现在都已经灭绝了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These animals were extinct,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.91,0:17:34.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过小型树懒仍然存在与今天的南美洲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but little sloths still existed in South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:37.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,一些体积较小的犰狳也是如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so did smaller armadillos.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:38.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着什么呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What could this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：他觉得他们非常相像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: It dawned on him that they resembled each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:43.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以，他认为这些被发现的化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,what he had found in the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.96,0:17:47.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,就是现在生活在南美洲的动物的祖先\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were the buried ancestors of the living animals of South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:52.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,这又是一个关于物种进化的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So,again,here was more evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.23,0:17:56.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,有力的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that species changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:59.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些动物的祖先经过漫长岁月的衍变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Somehow,these ancient giants must have been transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:05.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,成为了今天这些体积较小的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the smaller creatures we see today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.05,0:18:09.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是达尔文后来的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what Darwin would later find out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.18,0:18:12.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,把物种进化论发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}took this idea of how species change
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.99,0:18:16.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,成为人们的共识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a completely new league.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:22.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,在维多利亚女王的时代 科学家惯常地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In Victorian times,scientists routinely
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.06,0:18:27.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,从生物的胚胎期研究生命的成长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}studied life-forms at the embryonic stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.00,0:18:30.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些生物是如何从单个细胞成长为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How these tiny forms develop from just e single cell
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:35.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个完整的生命体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into an entire creature has long been seen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:39.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一直被视为自然的鬼斧神工的杰作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as one of the wonders of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.01,0:18:41.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,观察胚胎的成长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Watching a developing embryo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.05,0:18:43.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,实在是自然界最壮观、最惊人的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is truly the most glorious miracle of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.99,0:18:45.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，无以伦比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean,you know,no bologna.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.29,0:18:49.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,对胚胎的研究，使达尔文异常震惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: What Darwin learned from studying the embryos amazed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:55.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,在蛇的胚胎，你可以看到微小的隆起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In snake embryos,you could see tiny bumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:59.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些有着骨雏形的蛇蛋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bony rudiments of legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:02.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,却不会长成一个成年的蛇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But these would never develop in the adult snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.07,0:19:06.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文觉得很奇怪 蛇是因为某种原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin wondered,Were snakes somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.11,0:19:10.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,从别的会生蛋的动物衍变而来的吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}descended from animals with legs?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:19.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,他认识到成年的鲸鱼没有牙齿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He learned that whales,which have no teeth as adults,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.32,0:19:23.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是胚胎期的却有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had them as embryos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.09,0:19:29.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些牙齿在它们出生之前就消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those teeth disappeared before they were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.03,0:19:32.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,对达尔文而言，这意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To Darwin,it had to mean
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:36.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,鲸鱼是长着牙齿的生物的后裔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whales were descended from creatures with teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.17,0:19:42.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的胚胎则提供了更惊人的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But human embryos provided the most startling evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.21,0:19:45.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,在显微镜下面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Under the microscope,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:49.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,脖子的细小的夹缝清晰可见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tiny slits around the neck were clearly visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:53.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,和鱼类有着同样的特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Exactly the same structures were found in fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:58.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是鱼的夹缝变成了鳃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in fish,they turned into gills
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.16,0:20:02.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的则变成了内耳的骨头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In humans,they became the bones of our inner ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.10,0:20:11.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,这很明确的表示人类其实是鱼的后裔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Surely,this showed that humans must be descended from fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.31,0:20:15.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个让人震惊的想法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's an astonishing thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:19.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,贾德森：我不知道你的祖先，我的祖先\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}JUDSON: I don't know about your ancestors,but mine included
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.18,0:20:23.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,包括神父的，这是个大家通常都会猜想的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}priests and,you know,the,the usual,the usual suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.22,0:20:26.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是这个关乎我们全部人的研究发现指明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the idea that all of us have,have fish
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.29,0:20:28.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,鱼是我们家族的一员，实在是让人很惊讶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our family tree,I think it's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.32,0:20:32.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在，达尔文得出了一个惊人的结论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And so,Darwin arrived at an astonishing conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:37.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个对物种多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that would become central to his understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.10,0:20:39.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,有着的深刻理解的思想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the great diversity of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.33,0:20:43.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文得出惊人的大胆的结论---所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin had this amazingly bold idea-- the Tree of Life--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:46.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,所有的物种都是有联系的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that all species were connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.37,0:20:49.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着，只要你追溯历史足够远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what it meant was,it you go far enough back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:53.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,在我们人类家族里，你会发现祖先是条鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our family tree of humans,you'll come to fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.38,0:20:57.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,在鸟类的家族里 如果你追溯历史足够远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you go far enough back in the family tree of birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.25,0:21:01.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,你会发现祖先是条恐龙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll come to dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.12,0:21:03.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些看着非常不像的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that creatures that don't look
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.16,0:21:06.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,其实都是有着深刻的联系的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anything at all like each other are actually deeply connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:10.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,在达尔文之前 从来没有人得出这样的结论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one came close to having this idea before Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:14.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个对于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: This seemed to be an explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.40,0:21:17.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,生物多样性的解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the vast diversity of animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:19.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们有着共同的祖先\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beginning with a common ancestor,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:22.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,经过时间的推移\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over time across generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.34,0:21:26.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,物种发生了显著的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}species could change dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:29.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些增加了新的身体特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some might add new body features.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.25,0:21:32.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些则没有了某些特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others might drop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.39,0:21:34.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,最终，一个的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ultimately,one typo of creature
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.22,0:21:37.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,变成了各种各样不同的物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could be transformed into something utterly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.42,0:21:41.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个过程达尔文称之为：后代渐变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a process Darwin called "descent with modification."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.20,0:21:48.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是这就有问题了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bat it all begged a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.40,0:21:49.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是为什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.30,0:21:53.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,是什么促使生物改衍变？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was making creatures change?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:56.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文需要一些线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin needed clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.31,0:22:00.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在一个让人非常吃惊的地方找到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he found them in a very surprising place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.22,0:22:04.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,---狗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.45,0:22:08.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,大的、小的、肥的、高的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Big,small,fat,tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:13.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,英国人长期以来一直对它痴迷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The British have long been obsessed by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:18.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,在维多利亚女王时代的英国 人们对狗有着深深的喜爱之情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a full-blown love affair in Victorian England.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.27,0:22:27.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,甚至女皇也为狗而疯狂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even Her Majesty was dog crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.28,0:22:31.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种喜爱之情一直延续到现在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That love affair still continues today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.21,0:22:34.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,特别是在科学家之中，例如国家的卫生研究院的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Especially among scientists like Heidi Parker
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.42,0:22:36.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,海蒂·帕克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the National Institutes of Health.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.45,0:22:40.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个关于狗的最有趣的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,one of the most interesting things about dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.22,0:22:43.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,是狗产生了人类也有的变异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the kind of variation that you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.22,0:22:45.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,狗有像土拔鼠般大小的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have dogs the size of groundhogs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.33,0:22:47.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,有像可以长成骡子般大小的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}versus a dog like Zeppie,the Leonberger,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.43,0:22:49.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如莱昂贝格尔狗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who can get to be the size of a mule deer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.30,0:22:51.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们人类也有那种大小的差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It we had that kind of size variation in humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.37,0:22:55.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们会发现有些人就如奔走的芭比娃娃般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we would have people running around the size of Barbie dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.47,0:22:57.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,在那个时代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: In his day,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.44,0:23:01.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文知道这一系列的大小不同不是偶然出现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin knew this range of sizes hadn't come about by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.51,0:23:06.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是经过小心翼翼的选择过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Through a careful process of selection,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.45,0:23:08.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,狗饲养员对各种不同性状的狗进行杂交\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dog breeders mix different dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.38,0:23:12.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,长生了新品种的狗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with different physical traits to create new forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.26,0:23:17.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文认真思考他看到饲养员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin was intrigued by what he was seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:19.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,对这些狗所做的事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}breeders doing with the domestic dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.53,0:23:23.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们选择单个性征，例如大小或形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They could select for individual traits like size or shape,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.27,0:23:27.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,而它们会按着他们的想法而改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they could actually change their breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.50,0:23:30.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,例如 Whippe\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRTTOR: The Whippet,for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.24,0:23:33.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,被驯服去追逐兔子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had been developed to chase rabbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.34,0:23:37.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,它是由速度很快的灰狗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was created by mixing greyhounds for speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.24,0:23:41.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,和能狩猎的猎狗杂交而成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with terriers,used to hunt small game.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.42,0:23:46.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,这触动了达尔文\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then it hit Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.25,0:23:49.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有人类的干扰，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Was there a similar form of selection going on in nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.52,0:23:52.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,自然也是有着相似的选择功能吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but without human interference?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:54.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,自然的选择可以解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could natural selection
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.46,0:23:58.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,生物的多样性吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explain the great diversity of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.30,0:24:00.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：这太精彩了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: It was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.30,0:24:03.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,他把一些熟悉的、习以为常的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He took something very familiar and comfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.34,0:24:04.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,例如，动物的生育\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for example,animal breeding,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.47,0:24:07.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,解释这个在自然中同样进行的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and explained that the same sort of thing was going on in nature
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.41,0:24:11.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是这是在没有人类指引下进行的，节奏也有点不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just at a little bit different pace and with no human guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.52,0:24:20.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是到底是什么对自然来进行选择呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But what could be carrying out selection in the wild?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.42,0:24:24.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使得达尔文用全新的眼光来重新彻底看待自然\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was then that Darwin took a completely fresh look at nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.56,0:24:29.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,维多利亚时代关于自然的观点一直是令人信服的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Victorian view of nature was sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.56,0:24:33.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,那就是弱肉强食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lambs lay down with lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.40,0:24:36.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,但达尔文在贝格尔号的旅行中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Darwin's travels on the Beagle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.30,0:24:40.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,让他有了新的不同的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}led him to a different view.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.41,0:24:45.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,对达尔文而言，大自然是野蛮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For Darwin,nature was savage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.55,0:24:50.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,每个生物都在为生存而挣扎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every creature was locked in a desperate struggle for survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.35,0:24:57.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,而最终都以死亡结局\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ultimately ending in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.47,0:25:14.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,自然界生物死亡的规模的惊人而可怕的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The scale of death in nature is absolutely horrendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.41,0:25:20.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些时候不仅仅是死亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And sometimes it's not just that there's a lot of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.45,0:25:24.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,还是令人哀伤的死亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's very unpleasant death.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.46,0:25:37.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是在这残酷的混乱当中，达尔文看到了一个规律.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But in all this brutal chaos,Darwin saw a pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.63,0:25:42.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文揭示了自然界其实进行着一场战争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Darwin showed that nature was a battlefield
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.60,0:25:44.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,所有东西都在竞争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that everything was in competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.64,0:25:47.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这残酷的自然界的战争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this brutal battle,this war of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.47,0:25:51.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,正如达尔文描述的，实际上是一个富有创造性的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as Darwin described it,was actually a creative process.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.52,0:25:58.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文注意到的这个规律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The pattern that Darwin saw
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.62,0:26:02.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,揭示了能够生存下来的生物都是最能适应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was that the creatures that survived were those best adapted
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.49,0:26:06.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们所居住的独特的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}te the specific environments they lived in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.43,0:26:10.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,举个例子，有些生物要适应极端的气候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For instance,some could handle extremes of climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.47,0:26:19.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外一些是出色的捕杀机器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others were brilliantly honed killing machines,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.54,0:26:23.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,非常擅长捕捉猎物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perfect for catching the available prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.48,0:26:30.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,也有一些动物非常擅长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Still others were perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.45,0:26:34.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,去避开那些可能的猎杀者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to evade those who might be hunting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.46,0:26:38.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是这一关于大自然的残酷的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how did this harsh view of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.66,0:26:41.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,又是如何解释在加拉帕戈斯群岛上，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explain the finches on the Galapagos,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.46,0:26:45.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,正如达尔文所见到的那样，不同岛上的雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where Darwin observed that the birds on different islands
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.50,0:26:48.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,有不同形状的喙？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had different beak shapes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.57,0:26:51.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎样，这些不同的喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Somehow,those different beaks
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:55.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,有助于这些雀类的生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}must be helping the finches survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.68,0:27:00.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾：加拉帕格斯岛上的麻雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}TABIN: The finches of the Galapagos Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.68,0:27:04.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,有不同形状和大小的嘴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have beaks of many sizes and shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.45,0:27:05.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是有理由的：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there's a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.62,0:27:07.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们用嘴作为生存的工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They use their beaks as tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.55,0:27:10.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,想想看，有种强劲的工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now,if you think of the type of tool you would want
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.62,0:27:13.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,可以啄碎果实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to crush a seed that's very tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.73,0:27:15.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,而果实又是你的所好\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but is the food that you really like,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.73,0:27:17.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,你也会想要一个嘴巴巴，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd want a beak like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.60,0:27:21.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这种嘴正是地雀所拥有的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the type of beak the ground finch has.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.74,0:27:25.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,在这个小岛上，唯一的食物的是种子，极难啄碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On an island where the only food is seeds that are hard to crack,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.77,0:27:29.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,而一张短小而强劲的嘴巴即意味着可以生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a short,powerful beak will mean a finch will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.58,0:27:37.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是在其他的岛上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But on another island,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.65,0:27:41.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,可以食用的东四不是果实，而是花朵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the available food isn't seeds but flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.52,0:27:45.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想进入狭窄的区域，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It you wanted to get into narrow spaces to get pollen and nectar
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.73,0:27:47.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,吮吸极难吸食的花粉和花蜜，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are very hard to get at,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.73,0:27:50.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,你需要的不是个巨大坚硬的嘴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you wouldn't need a big,strong beak,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.46,0:27:51.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是个锐利的嘴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd need a probing beak.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.50,0:27:53.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以，不同的岛上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So,on a different island,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.57,0:27:55.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,食物不尽相同，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where you have a different food source,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.64,0:27:57.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,而鸟雀们也就有着不同的嘴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have a different beak shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.50,0:28:01.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这种现象在加拉帕格斯群岛上司空见惯.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this pattern was repeated across the Galapagos.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.61,0:28:05.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,这么看来，似乎雀喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seems that the finches' beaks
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.51,0:28:09.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,已经适应了不同岛屿的特殊食物类型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had altered to fit the diet of each particular island.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.52,0:28:12.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,这也就是为什么最初的一种鸟雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that was how one original type of finch
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.72,0:28:16.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,而衍变为后来的多种鸟雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had been transformed into many.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.50,0:28:28.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是这些变化是如何产生的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how had these changes come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.71,0:28:36.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,这不，达尔文又掌握了另外一条线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}here,Darwin had another clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.58,0:28:40.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,这他在他自己的家族中也发现了这点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He could see it in his own family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.78,0:28:43.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像父辈们知道的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As every parent knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.55,0:28:47.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,并没有两个孩子是完全一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no two children are ever exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.69,0:28:50.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文和他哥哥伊拉斯莫斯长得就不一样，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charles looked different from his brother,Erasmus,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.79,0:28:53.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,尽管他们父母一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even though they shared the same parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.76,0:28:57.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文的儿女们也看上去不像他和他妻子艾玛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Charles's children looked a bit like him and his wife Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.77,0:29:04.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且他们看起来都各不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they too looked different from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.77,0:29:08.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着在他们身上有了某种变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was something he called variation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.68,0:29:11.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,他意识到并不是一个人出现这种情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He realized that not every individual was the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.71,0:29:14.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种情况 很常见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stamped out like a toy from a press.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.68,0:29:16.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是确实有着不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there was variation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.72,0:29:19.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Darwin realized that variation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.72,0:29:23.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种衍变一定是大自然产生变化的起点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}must be the starting point for change in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.76,0:29:26.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,任何的物种，即使是寄生在垃圾里的生物，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In any generation,the animals in a litter
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.83,0:29:30.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,都各不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are never quite the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.57,0:29:34.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,而在大自然，这种微小的不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in the wild,such a tiny variation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.70,0:29:38.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,便意味着生与死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}might make all the difference between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.64,0:29:43.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,打个比方说，两只企鹅在脂肪厚度上，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Two penguins,for instance,might differ a tiny bit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.84,0:29:46.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,也许会有细微差别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the thickness of their blubber--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.81,0:29:50.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,这对极寒生活可关键了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a big factor if you live in extreme cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.65,0:29:54.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,在恶劣的气候中，环境会选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a harsh climate,the environment will select
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.66,0:29:58.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,谁能生存，而谁又将死去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who will live and who will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.66,0:30:02.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,慢慢地，达尔文认为，经过很多代繁衍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And slowly,Darwin suggested,over many,many generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.66,0:30:07.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种微小的衍变使得适者生存，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these tiny variations would allow the fit to get fitter
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.87,0:30:12.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,而不适者则湮灭在时间的洪流中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the unfit would vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.84,0:30:16.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些变化一点点积累，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These variations accumulate
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.91,0:30:20.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,最终，新的物种便分开了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and eventually,new species branch off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.75,0:30:24.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是物竞天择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is evolution by natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.62,0:30:28.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是新物种诞生的其中一个关键因素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is one of the keys to how new species are formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.66,0:30:36.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,在肺结核困扰的八年时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ank so,in 1859,after years of painstaking research,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.80,0:30:41.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文终于发表了他的著作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin finally published his masterwork,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.94,0:30:44.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,--- 《物种起源》.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the Origin of  Species.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.67,0:30:48.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,任何赞誉之词都不为过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is still impossible to overstate its importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.88,0:30:51.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一部真正意义上的划时代的的杰作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was really a quantum advance in understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.91,0:30:55.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,它使人们为之一振，彻底颠覆了人们的观念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It shook people up,it changed the way people thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.85,0:30:58.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,过去那种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Gone was the idea that all species
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.92,0:31:01.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,所有物种都是完美而万古不易的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were created perfect and immutable,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.86,0:31:04.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,人们曾作为信条的陈腐观点一去不复返了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taken as an article of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.73,0:31:08.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,在这基础上，达尔文提出了合理的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In its place,Darwin provided a proper scientific theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.66,0:31:14.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,以观察事实为基础的科学理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}based on facts and observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:17.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可比远远不止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is much more than the presentation of simply
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.77,0:31:19.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,是简单的自然选择说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the idea of natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.94,0:31:22.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是，这是一种对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is a,it's a vision
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.81,0:31:24.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,自然选择是如何产生进化的绝妙猜想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of how evolution by natural selection works.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.85,0:31:28.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,150年后，达尔文的理论经受住了时间的考验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}150 years later,his theory has stood the test of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.75,0:31:33.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文观点是如此地准确无误，这真令人惊叹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARR0LL: What's amazing is that Darwin got so much right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.72,0:31:37.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文的进化论基本上至今仍然不可撼动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His ideas largely stay intact today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.83,0:31:41.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而，达尔文自己\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But Darwin himself
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.00,0:31:45.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,也承认他的进化论还存在缺陷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}acknowledged that there were holes in his theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.84,0:31:52.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,他并不知道其作用机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He didn't actually know how it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.78,0:32:00.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,他也不知道生物体内到底在发生着什么变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was happening inside a creature's body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.81,0:32:04.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,使得生物产生变异？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that makes it change?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.95,0:32:08.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,如今，现代科学通过揭示达尔文不曾想到的隐藏机制，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now,at last,modern science is providing the answers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.89,0:32:13.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,将对这一问题提供答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through a hidden mechanism that Darwin knew nothing about
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.77,0:32:27.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,皮纳卡特沙漠，位于亚利桑那州，那儿环境恶劣而严酷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Arizona's Pinacarte Desert is a harsh and brutal place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.94,0:32:32.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是岩小囊鼠，更能体会到这点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Especially if you're a rock pocket mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.92,0:32:38.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,纳赫曼：这些老鼠就像是沙漠里的士力架巧克力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NACHMAN: They're the Snickers bar of the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.79,0:32:40.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可是真的，他们几乎成为所有生物的猎物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They really are,they're eaten by everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.02,0:32:43.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们可能被狐狸或者土狼吃掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're probably eaten by foxes and coyotes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.99,0:32:47.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,抑或是响尾蛇和猫头鹰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and rattlesnakes,owls.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.89,0:32:49.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,岩小囊鼠只有半盎司重，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Weighing just half an ounce,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.76,0:32:52.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种老鼠在那些大型捕食者面前，简直是不堪一击.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this mouse could never fight off these large predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.87,0:32:56.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了生存，最好的办法就是伪装\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its best hope for survival is camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.80,0:32:58.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,不足为奇地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.94,0:33:02.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,岩小囊鼠的皮毛与皮纳卡特的岩石颜色类似，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its fur matches the color of the Pinacarte rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.98,0:33:06.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而，在沙漠的某些地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in some sections of the desert,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.88,0:33:10.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,环境有所不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the environment is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.92,0:33:14.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,远古火山的喷发，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ancient volcanoes erupted
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.02,0:33:15.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,使得如今的沙漠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now the desert is a patchwork
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.96,0:33:19.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,布满了黑熔岩及浅色岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of dark lava and light rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.96,0:33:24.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,显然，浅色皮毛的老鼠在黑熔岩上的话，很容易就成为猎物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But of course,a light mouse on a dark rock is easy pickings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.07,0:33:32.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此，有些事情发生了，也许达尔文也预料到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,something has happened that Darwin might have predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.88,0:33:40.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,生活在黑熔岩中的小鼠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mice now living on the dark rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.05,0:33:43.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们的皮毛已经进化成了深色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have evolved darker fur.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.95,0:33:47.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,而那些生活在浅色岩石中的老鼠依然是毛发浅浅的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those that stayed on the light rocks remain light.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.79,0:33:56.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,迈克尔.纳赫曼被深深吸引住了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Michael Nachman was fascinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.93,0:33:58.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是怎么发生的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How had this happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.06,0:34:02.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了找寻答案，他首先得逮些老鼠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To find out,he first needed to catch some mice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.04,0:34:03.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此，他和肖恩卡罗尔一起，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,with Sean Carroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.80,0:34:06.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,去查看他前一晚放置的捕鼠陷阱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he visits a line of traps he set the previous night.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.84,0:34:08.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,纳赫曼：所有的黑毛老鼠的小腹都是白色的，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NACHMAN: All of the dark ones have a white underbelly
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.94,0:34:11.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,想必腹部黑色是不需要经过自然选择的吧，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and presumably,there's no selection for dark on the belly
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.88,0:34:14.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为那些捕食者多从上方捕杀老鼠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because predators are going,coming from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.08,0:34:16.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个达尔文可能也做过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: This much Darwin could have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.85,0:34:19.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,找到了一些老鼠，并将他们皮毛的颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Find some mice and compare the color of their fur
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.99,0:34:21.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,和周围环境相比较\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to their environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.86,0:34:23.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,而纳赫曼现在可以做点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Nachman can now do something
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.12,0:34:24.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文从未做过的事儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Darwin never could.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.96,0:34:28.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,他可以深入观察动物的DNA.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He can look inside the animal's DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.94,0:34:40.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,对DNA的研究是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The study of DNA is one
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.07,0:34:44.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,现代科学的一项伟大胜利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the great triumphs of modern science.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.11,0:34:48.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,它把我们对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has taken our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.85,0:34:50.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,生物的进化和发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of how creatures evolve and develop
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.88,0:34:54.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,引领到一个连达尔文从未想过的境地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a level that Darwin could never have dreamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.06,0:34:59.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：DNA分子是生命的真正秘密之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: The DNA molecule is one of the real secrets of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.89,0:35:00.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是个完美的系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a perfect system
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.93,0:35:02.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,储存了大量的控制所有生物必要组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for storing the vast amounts of information
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.13,0:35:06.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,的遗传信息.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's necessary for building all kinds of creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.10,0:35:13.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,DNA由一条长分子链组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: DNA consists of one long molecule
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.07,0:35:17.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,以双螺旋式结构盘旋着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spiraling around in a double helix.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.08,0:35:23.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,螺旋结构依次由四个碱基构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That helix is,in turn,made up of four smaller molecules,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:29.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,分别称为腺嘌呤A 鸟嘌呤G 胸腺嘧啶T 胞嘧啶C\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called by the letters G,A,T and C.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.16,0:35:35.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,在每个生物的细胞内都可以发现DNA的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DNA can be found in the cells of every living thing on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.90,0:35:42.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,贾德森：我认为DNA的惊人之处在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}JUDSON: The thing about DNA that I think is remarkable
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.17,0:35:46.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,其DNA分子本身，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that the molecule itself is so elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.94,0:35:50.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是几个简单的碱基，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With a small number of letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.04,0:35:54.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,却蕴涵着无穷的信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can say almost infinite words.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.98,0:35:58.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,这才是关键所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And that is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.18,0:36:02.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,DNA 是人体内遗传密码，有两条链组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DNA is a code and its double strand contains
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.09,0:36:05.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些信息组成了各种性状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the information to make living things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.16,0:36:08.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定生物的生长和发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}grow and develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.06,0:36:11.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,DNA分子中分布着的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lined along each DNA molecule are ranged
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.10,0:36:15.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,组成基因的特殊序列.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}special sequences of this code that form our genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.18,0:36:27.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,而很多基因最终变成了蛋白质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many genes get translated into proteins.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.08,0:36:34.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些蛋白质构成了身体的基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these proteins make the stuff of our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.12,0:36:38.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一种构成了头发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One protein makes hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.16,0:36:41.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外一种则构成软骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another makes cartilage.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.03,0:36:44.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有的组成肌肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others make muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.10,0:36:45.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：DNA 神奇之处在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: What makes DNA so amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.20,0:36:49.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,它仅仅包含四种碱基，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that it just contains four letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.10,0:36:52.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这四种碱基的各种不同组合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but all sorts of combinations of those four letters
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.01,0:36:53.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,却包含了构成这个星球上所有生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}contains all the information for making
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.97,0:36:57.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,的所有信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the creatures that are on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.04,0:36:59.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,某种基因决定了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: It's a gene that determines
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.05,0:37:02.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们的眼睛是蓝色的还是其他颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether our eyes are blue or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.12,0:37:05.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,其他一些基因使我们产生雀斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another gives us freckles.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.02,0:37:08.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,另一些基因则让我们脸上出现酒窝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another gives us dimples.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.12,0:37:13.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是DNA 也有个非常重要的特征，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But DNA has one other vital quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.20,0:37:19.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,它不会一成不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't stay the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.23,0:37:23.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,（哭泣声）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(crying)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.20,0:37:27.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,孕育婴儿时，受精卵\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a baby is conceived,the fertilized egg receives
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.14,0:37:31.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,从母体和父体分别获得一半DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}half its DNA from the mother and half from the father,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.18,0:37:35.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,从而创造出一个全新的组合体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating wholly new combinations.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.05,0:37:37.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么孩子会跟双亲长相略有相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's why we look a bit like our parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.28,0:37:41.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,却又不尽相同.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but also different.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.02,0:37:48.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,另一种DNA产生变化的方式就是突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another way that DNA can change is mutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.17,0:37:54.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：突变是进化过程中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Mutation is a critical ingredient
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.20,0:37:56.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,另一个关键因素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the recipe for evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.07,0:37:59.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有突变的话，大自然的一切将保持一致性，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without mutation,everything would stay constant
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.04,0:38:00.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,一代代相传\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generation after generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.17,0:38:04.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,而突变会产生变种，使得个体产生差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mutation generates variation,differences between individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.18,0:38:10.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,当细胞分裂及机体发育时，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Mutations can happen as our DNA copies itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.15,0:38:14.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,DNA会自我复制，而突变也即在这个过程发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when our cells divide and our bodies develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.09,0:38:19.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,例如腺嘌呤A可能被鸟嘌呤G替代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An "A" for instance,can be replaced by a "G"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.33,0:38:22.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,或者胞嘧啶C 变为胸腺嘧啶T\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or a "C" by a"T."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.10,0:38:26.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些都将导致不可预知的突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This can cause minute changes that no one is even aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.33,0:38:30.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,在突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when mutations occur
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.10,0:38:33.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,在我们传给后代的细胞内发生微小变化时，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the cells we pass down to our chindren,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.11,0:38:37.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,却能引起机体产生极大的变化.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can cause big changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.15,0:38:45.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像使浅色老鼠颜色变深一样.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like turning a light-colored mouse dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.15,0:38:49.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,突变似乎意味着坏事的发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Mutation" seems to mean that something bad has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.22,0:38:52.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,而对机体而言，突变很难说是好的，还是坏的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well,mutations are neither good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.09,0:38:52.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,突变是否受欢迎，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whether they are favored,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:55.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,或遭到抗拒、抑或保持中立\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or whether they are rejected,or whether they're just neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.30,0:38:59.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,这主要由机体所处的条件决定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depends upon the conditions an organism finds itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.10,0:39:00.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,对于小囊鼠来说，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So for the pocket mouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.10,0:39:02.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,它产生了毛色变黑的突变.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mutation that caused the mouse to turn black...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.30,0:39:04.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,这对于生活在黑熔岩的老鼠来说，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is good if you're living
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.10,0:39:06.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,是有益的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on black rock,it's bad if you're living
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.27,0:39:10.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,而对生活在沙质沙漠中的老鼠来说则是不好的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out in the sandy desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.08,0:39:12.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,正是突变，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: It was that mutation,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.31,0:39:15.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,使得浅色老鼠变黑，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one that turned a light-colored mouse dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.08,0:39:19.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这也正是纳赫曼所探寻的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Michael Nachman was hunting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.39,0:39:28.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,回到实验室后，他开始了艰辛的工作，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in the lab,he began the painstaking business
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.13,0:39:32.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,通过比较两种老鼠的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of comparing the genes of the two types of mice,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.20,0:39:35.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,试图找出其中的差异.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trying to pinpoint any differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.13,0:39:36.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,纳赫曼：当你真的不知道你会发现什么的时候，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NACHMAN: Science is fun
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.27,0:39:40.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学变得非常有趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you really don't know what you're going to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.28,0:39:49.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,通过逐个检查两只老鼠的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: One by one the genes in the two nice
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.22,0:39:52.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,发现完全一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}proved identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.25,0:39:56.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是同时，他在一个基因里发现了一些东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then,in one gene,he found something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.39,0:40:00.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因序列中，有四个地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were four places where the sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.39,0:40:04.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,的“A”、“T”、“C”、和“G”不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of"A's," "f's," and "G's" were different..
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.23,0:40:10.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,当一只老鼠出生的时候就伴随着这些基因突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a mouse is born with these mutations,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.34,0:40:14.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,它的毛就长成了黑色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its fur grows dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.38,0:40:19.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个意味着它可以在黑色的岩石里生存下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that means it can survive on the dark rocks
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.41,0:40:22.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,而其他的并不可以存活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when others would not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.42,0:40:25.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是一个很清楚的例子，证明了进化论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here wes a clear example of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.42,0:40:29.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,和自然选择确实在发生作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and natural selection at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.39,0:40:34.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想达尔文应该会很高兴的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think Darwin would have been delighted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.19,0:40:36.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果他知道我们找到了这些基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to know that we can find the genes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.33,0:40:40.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,导致了进化的逐渐改变的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are responsible for evolutionary change.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.33,0:40:44.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,这只是人们找到的基因突变和进化之间关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And this was just one of many links
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.30,0:40:48.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,中的其中一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that have been found between genetic mutations and evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.34,0:40:52.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们现在可以很精确地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists can now pinpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.38,0:40:56.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,用行动来描述关于进化论的一连串例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a range of examples of evolution in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.35,0:41:02.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,疣猴可以辨认颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Colobus monkey can see in color
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.29,0:41:04.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,这都是由于一个基因上的突变而引起的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of a mutation in one gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.46,0:41:08.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,它现在可以从一堆硬邦邦的绿色老叶子中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can now tell nutritious red leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.29,0:41:12.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,分辨出有营养的红色叶子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from tough,old green ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.20,0:41:15.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个基因的小故障使得这些南极的鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A genetic glitch gave this Antarctic fish
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.34,0:41:18.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,血液有了强效的防冻剂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a potent antifreeze in its blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.24,0:41:20.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以它可以在冰水里存活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it can survive in the icy waters
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.44,0:41:23.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,而其他的鱼则不行.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when others cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.44,0:41:25.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因突变和进化之间的这种联系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So powerful was this link between
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.48,0:41:29.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,非常显然而强有力，而这也就引出了一种观点的形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}genetic mutation and evolution that an idea took hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.48,0:41:34.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,即要想理解进化论是怎么发挥作用的，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To understand how evolution works,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.32,0:41:38.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,你所需做的事情就是对比所有生物的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all you need to do is compare creatures' genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.31,0:41:56.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,有人可能会认为要弄清楚所有的物种演变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One might think that you could understand all of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.28,0:41:58.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,只需要确定每种生物的基因位置即可\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}simgly by mapping the genes of every creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.51,0:42:01.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,识别所有的基因，区分所有的区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Identify all the genes,identify all the differences
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.45,0:42:04.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后就可以解释不同生物的千差万别了，例如\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you could explain the differences between,say,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.45,0:42:08.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,老鼠、猴子和人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mouse and monkeys and humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.32,0:42:11.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以当人类基因组计划在1990年开始实施的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So when the Human Genome Project began in 1999,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.42,0:42:15.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,整个科学世界一片震动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the scientific world was on tenterhooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.29,0:42:17.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类总共有三十多亿的DNA碱基序列\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All three billion letters of our DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.50,0:42:20.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,得陆续地鉴定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were going to be identified in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.50,0:42:23.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时，有一些动物的DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In parallel,the DNA of some animals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.47,0:42:25.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,和植物的也被拿来排序鉴定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and plants was also being sequenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.41,0:42:29.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,显然，这对我们对不同的生命体是怎么进化来的这一方面的认知\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Surely,this would be a quantum leap in our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.31,0:42:33.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,将会是一个巨大的突破\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of how different life-forms evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.51,0:42:37.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这又引出了另一观点：像我们人类一样的复杂的动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With this came another idea: that complex animals like us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.42,0:42:41.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,会比简单的动物具有更多的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have many more genes than simpler ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.52,0:42:44.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,而我们人类，则是这个星球上最复杂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here we are,the most complex
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.29,0:42:46.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,和最精细的动物，对吧？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sophisticated animal on the planet,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.43,0:42:47.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,或许你会认为这个观点需要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You might think that would require
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.53,0:42:50.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,更多基因信息来证实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a whole lot more genetic information.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.30,0:42:51.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,论断已经下了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The betting was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.60,0:42:55.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是我们人类的基因组相对于其他生命体来说到底有多大呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just how big would our genome be compared to other life-forms?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.54,0:42:58.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,据估计，人类有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were estimates that humans would have
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.44,0:43:02.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,8万到12万个基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between,let's say,80,000 and 120,000 genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.55,0:43:14.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以当最终结果在2003年出来的时候，所有人都震惊了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So when the final answer came in 2003,it was a shocker.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.33,0:43:23.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类只有23000个基因 --- 就跟一只鸡所拥有的数量一模一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}23,000 genes--the same number as a chicken...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.40,0:43:32.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,比一串玉米的数量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}less than an ear of corn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.41,0:43:34.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,莱文：我的意思是，当发现人类的基因那么少的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}LEVINE: I mean,people were freaked out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.57,0:43:37.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,人们完全震惊了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the relatively small number of genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.54,0:43:41.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类基因组中，只有大概22000到23000个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's down to something like 22,000 or 23,000
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.45,0:43:44.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,蛋白编码基因.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}protein-coding genes in the human genome.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.42,0:43:47.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,简单的线虫拥有大概相同的数量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The simple nematode worm has about that same number.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.59,0:43:51.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,相对于人类的基因组而言，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are plants that have considerably more genes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.36,0:43:54.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,也有一些植物有多得多的基因组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the glorious human genome.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.39,0:43:55.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,整个人类基因组计划似乎成为了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The whole human genome project has been
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.53,0:43:57.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,一次令人羞愧的尝试，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a humbling experience,as we've discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.60,0:44:00.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为事实上，我们并未发现最先期望的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that,actually,it doesn't take as many genes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.50,0:44:02.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么多组成人类的基因.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make a human as we had all hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.50,0:44:06.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,这还不仅仅是说我们只拥有那么少的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And it wasn't just that we had so few genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.61,0:44:10.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,而问题是很多关键基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but many of our key genes were identical
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.41,0:44:14.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,尽然和其他动物的完全一样.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to those of other animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.41,0:44:16.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这已然是个重大突破，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Huge though the breakthrough had been,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.48,0:44:18.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因革命开启了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the genetic revolution had opened up
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.55,0:44:21.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,一系列全新谜题的探究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a whole new set of puzzles.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.52,0:44:24.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,作为一个解开进化论原理这个谜底的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a solution to the mystery of how evolution works,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.66,0:44:28.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因和突变只是整个故事的一小部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}genes and their mutations were only part of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.57,0:44:36.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中肯定还有其他一些更难以捉摸的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There had to be something else more subtle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.44,0:44:38.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,和更加神秘的东西.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and more mysterious going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.54,0:44:40.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：我们接下来需要解释的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: We have to explain then,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.54,0:44:42.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,如何在一系列非常相似的基因中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How do you get all these differences
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.51,0:44:46.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,找出其中的区别.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you have really similar sets of genes?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.41,0:44:47.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,探索那些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The quest to uncover
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.48,0:44:51.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文从来都不知道的发现又得从头再来了.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what Darwin never knew would have to start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.49,0:44:59.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,最初的比较有意义的结论来自那些生命体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first tantalizing clues would come from those life-forms
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.66,0:45:03.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文早已研究过了 --- 胚胎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Darwin himself had studied: embryos.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.63,0:45:07.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,看看这些胚胎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Look at these embryos.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.50,0:45:11.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,在刚开始怀孕的日子里简直不可能去分辨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is almost impossible to tell just days after conception
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.54,0:45:13.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪个是小鸡，哪个是海龟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the chicken,the turtle,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.71,0:45:16.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪个是蝙蝠，以及哪个是人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the bat,the human.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.64,0:45:20.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们看上去几乎一模一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They look almost the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.42,0:45:26.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,只有当他们长大了才变得清晰到底什么是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only as they grow does it become clear which is which.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.62,0:45:30.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,正如现在的科学家一样，达尔文疑惑的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin wondered,as scientists do today,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.59,0:45:33.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么他们可以在开始的时候这么相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could they start out so similar
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.46,0:45:37.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,而在最后却这么不同呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and end up so different?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.70,0:45:40.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,莱文：在胚胎告诉我们的事情中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}LEVINE: There is something profound
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.43,0:45:41.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,这里面肯定有意义深远的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about what the embryo was telling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.70,0:45:45.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且我们已经再次发现达尔文到所说过的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we have rediscovered what Darwin was talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.51,0:45:50.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,胚胎是产生动物多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all along,that the embryo's  where the action is,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.48,0:45:51.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,的关键所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in terms of animal diversity,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.64,0:45:55.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,胚胎是产生多样性的平台\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is the platform for diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.48,0:46:00.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,使现代生物学家觉深深着迷的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: What fascinates modern biologists
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.72,0:46:03.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,是所有这些不同的动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that all these different animals
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.46,0:46:05.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,尽管看上去不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}don't just look the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.49,0:46:09.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,却使用着几乎同样的关键基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they are using virtually the same set of key genes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.50,0:46:13.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,来塑造他们的躯体.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to build their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.60,0:46:19.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,躯体决定基因控制着大脑的生长部位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The body plan genes determine where the head goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.57,0:46:23.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,四肢的生长部位，以及它们会有什么样的外形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the limbs go,and what form they take--
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.61,0:46:25.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪里是手臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether they are arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.61,0:46:29.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,大腿或者翅膀.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}legs or wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.62,0:46:32.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外一组基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another set of genes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.69,0:46:35.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定着动物的身体形态：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}determines an animal's body patterning:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.55,0:46:37.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,皮肤上的疹斑、条纹以及斑点.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the blotches,the stripes and spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.72,0:46:41.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,都是同样的基因在所有的动物上起的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is the same genes at work in every creature
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.76,0:46:45.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,从豹子到孔雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the leopard to the peacock
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.60,0:46:48.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,再到果蝇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the fruit fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.57,0:46:52.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且在它们身上产生了完全不同的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet they produce radically different results.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.61,0:47:00.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使得科学家们在动物的身体是怎么变异的这一方面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This has led sciectists to a crucial insight
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.55,0:47:02.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,有了一个更深刻的理解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about how animal bodies have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.62,0:47:06.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是由于基因的数量多少起作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not the number of genes that counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.62,0:47:09.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：不是你所拥有的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: It's not the genes you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.56,0:47:11.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是你怎么使用这些基因，进而形成了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but how you use them that generates
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.56,0:47:14.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,动物王国的多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the great diversity of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.69,0:47:17.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,找出这些同样的基因是怎么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Finding out just how these same genes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.66,0:47:20.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,用来创造这么令人吃惊的多样性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are used to create such amazing diversity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.77,0:47:23.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,这正是肖恩.卡罗尔以及\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been the work of Sean Carroll
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.80,0:47:27.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,不像一个现在科学的英雄---果蝇，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and an unlikely hero of modern science.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.71,0:47:34.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,所从事的工作.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fruit fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.58,0:47:37.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,我非常想要到非洲草原上去研究那里的哺乳动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As much as I'd like to study the mammals of the African Savannah,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.82,0:47:39.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们比实验室里的动物拥有更少的选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they make poor choices for laboratory animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.82,0:47:43.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们体积庞大 昂贵同时它们繁殖得非常缓慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're large,expensive and they reproduce very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.72,0:47:47.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了拿到数据，我们只有找最简单的例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get data,we have to find the simplest examples
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.69,0:47:51.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些例子跟我们想要了解现象相联系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the phenomenon we want to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.60,0:47:54.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是这些卑微的果蝇却是一种不可思议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But the humble fruit fly does weird
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.63,0:47:58.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,和有趣的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.67,0:48:03.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,果蝇只为异性舞蹈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This fruit fly is dancing for sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.78,0:48:08.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,一只全神贯注的母果蝇正在表演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A rapt female takes in the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.68,0:48:11.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,她被公果蝇翅膀上的黑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She's particularly besotted
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.75,0:48:15.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,深深吸引.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the dark spots on the male's wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.82,0:48:19.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,肖恩.卡罗尔也同样陶醉地看着他.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Watching it all is an equally besotted Sean Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.66,0:48:21.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：你可能觉得他们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: You might think them
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.66,0:48:23.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,是有点令人讨厌，但是它们真的很迷人.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just be annoying,but they're really charming.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.80,0:48:25.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个物种的公果蝇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the males of this species
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.63,0:48:26.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,演出了一场精心设计的求爱舞蹈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}does a rather elaborate courtship dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.73,0:48:30.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在那些女性面前展示这些斑斓的翅膀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where he displays these spotted wings in front of the female.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.74,0:48:35.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,对我们来说，它就像一只孔雀一样华丽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To us,it's as magnificent as what a peacock does.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.88,0:48:42.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是果蝇的某些种系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But in some species of fruit fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.65,0:48:46.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,公果蝇没有翅斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the males don't have wing spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.72,0:48:48.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：这是另外一种果蝇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: There's another fruit fly species
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.79,0:48:51.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟那些翅斑果蝇不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's different from the spotted species
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.79,0:48:52.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们有两点不同：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in two important ways:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.93,0:48:55.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,它的翅膀没有斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it doesn't have spots on its wings
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.69,0:48:57.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,它也不常会那么跳舞.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it does a lot less dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.63,0:49:00.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,这，是一个经典的进化论谜题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Here,then,is a classic evolutionary puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.87,0:49:04.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么有一种果蝇有翅斑而另外一种没有呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why does one type of fly have spots and the other doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.81,0:49:06.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,肖恩.卡罗尔想要弄明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sean Carroll wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.91,0:49:10.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们的基因发生了什么使得它们不一样呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is going on in their genes that makes them different?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.81,0:49:13.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：所以我们想要使用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: So we wanted to take apart
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.71,0:49:14.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究翅斑的基因机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the genetic machinery for making wing spots
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.91,0:49:18.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,来弄明白到底这些翅斑是怎么进化的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to understand how those wing spots evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.79,0:49:25.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔开始了一个课程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Carroll began the process of sifting through
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.66,0:49:27.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个课题是筛选果蝇的DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the two types of flies' DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.69,0:49:30.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,他有一条线索，使得他开始了他的研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had one clue to set him on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.93,0:49:34.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,他已经知道黑翅斑是怎样由基因编码成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He already knew the gene that codes for the black wing spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.84,0:49:39.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,他把它称作“画笔基因”\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He calls it the"paintbrush gene."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.87,0:49:42.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,但奇怪的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.84,0:49:46.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,当他比较两只果蝇的基因的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when he compared the genes of the two flies,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.78,0:49:48.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们都有这个基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they both had that gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.75,0:49:52.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是，仅有一只果蝇有斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet,only one had spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.82,0:49:56.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：当我们观察这两种物种的基因的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: When we look at that gene in the two species,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.92,0:49:59.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们真的都有这种基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really they both have this paintbrush gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.69,0:50:00.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以差异在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.76,0:50:02.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是说它们有没有这个基因，而是它们是如何使用它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not having the gene,it's how they use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.83,0:50:06.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一只在翅膀里使用它来长出斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One species uses it in the wing to make spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.90,0:50:11.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,而另外一只没有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The other one doesn't .
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.87,0:50:16.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而为什么同种基因在一种果蝇上长出斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So why did the paintbrush gene create spots in one type of fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.74,0:50:22.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,却另一只没有？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not in the other?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.78,0:50:24.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了寻找答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In search ot answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.95,0:50:28.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔转而研究大家了解最少的DNA另一部分：\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carroll turned to one of the least understand regions of DNA:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.72,0:50:32.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,一度被广泛认为是“垃圾”的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the vast stretches that were once known as"junk."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.87,0:50:43.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,被称作基因组的暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has been called the dark matter of the genome.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.74,0:50:47.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,神秘莫测的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.84,0:50:49.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,未可知的，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Uncharted.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.88,0:50:51.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,奇奇怪怪的.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.74,0:50:53.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,双螺旋结构的大部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The vast bulk of the double helix,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.98,0:50:57.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,它有98%不会编码成蛋白质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some 98% of it,doesn't code for proteins,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.88,0:51:00.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,而蛋白质是组成我们身体的主要物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which make the stuff of our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.72,0:51:04.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,而基因只占2%.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The genes which do,comprise just two percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.99,0:51:08.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,甚至到现在也没有人可以确定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even now,no one is sure
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.86,0:51:12.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些巨大的没有编码的区域实际起的大部分作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what much of this huge non-coding area actually does,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.97,0:51:14.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,但它长久以来就吸引着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it has long beckoned
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.83,0:51:17.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,像肖恩.卡罗尔这样的基因突变探究者.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}evolutionary detectives,like Sean Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.87,0:51:18.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个弯管\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,this is a bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.97,0:51:20.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些用来测试基因片段的？ 是的.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the fragment to test. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.87,0:51:24.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔已经发现斑点的基因本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Carroll had already learned that the paintbrush gene itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.91,0:51:26.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,在两种果蝇中是完全一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was identical in the two types of fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.81,0:51:29.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以他深入研究果蝇的DNA.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So he extended his search through their DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.92,0:51:33.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,就在斑点基因的外面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in one place,just outside the paintbrush gene,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.79,0:51:38.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,他发现了一条重要的线索.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he found an important clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.89,0:51:40.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,有个DNA的片段跟带翅斑果蝇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A stretch of DNA that was different
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.96,0:51:42.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,中的不一样.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the fly with wing spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.90,0:51:46.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What could this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.87,0:51:52.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以卡罗尔进行了一次实验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So Carroll conducted an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.94,0:51:54.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,他决定把带翅斑果蝇中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He decided to put that mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.91,0:51:58.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,找到的那个DNA片段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stretch of DNA that he had found in the spotted fly
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.84,0:52:02.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,植入不带翅斑的果蝇身上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the unspotted fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.05,0:52:04.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了弄清这个基因是否起作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To help him see it it had any effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.85,0:52:06.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,他把这以DNA片段和水母的一个基因连在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he attended it to a gene from a jellyfish,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.99,0:52:10.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种基因能编码出使水母发光的蛋白质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a gene that codes for a protein that makes the jellyfish glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.86,0:52:14.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们把这一DNA切成很小的片段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We cut the DNA up into little pieces,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.83,0:52:17.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们把其中一些放到一个可以在黑暗中发光的蛋白质里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we hook it up to a protein that glows in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.86,0:52:21.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后再把这个植入不带翅斑的果蝇身上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then we inject that into the unspotted fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.04,0:52:26.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,接着，一些不寻常地事情发生了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And then,something remarkable happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.97,0:52:31.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：当我们观察那些无翅斑的果蝇的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: When me looked at those unspotted flies,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.01,0:52:34.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在看到它们的翅膀在黑暗中发出一些斑点的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see now their wings are glowing in the dark with spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.95,0:52:39.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些神秘的DNA的片段不知怎么的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRTOR: Somehow that mysterious stretch of DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.82,0:52:42.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,已经启动了不带翅斑果蝇中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had turned on the paintbrush gene
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.02,0:52:44.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些斑点基因.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the unspotted fly's wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.82,0:52:48.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,曾经不带翅斑，而今它拥有可以发光的翅斑.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once spotless,now it had luminous spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.03,0:52:50.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：我们成功了！\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.00,0:52:54.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经发现这些起作用的DNA的片段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'd found the piece of DNA that mattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.07,0:52:57.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔已经发现了一些东西可以颠覆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Carroll had found something that is revolutionizing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.10,0:52:59.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们对动物体内基因突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our understanding of how different
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.97,0:53:01.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,千变万化的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}animal bodies have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.87,0:53:05.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,有一小块称作“开关”的DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A piece of DNA called a "switch."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.98,0:53:09.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这些开关并不是基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Switches are not genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.98,0:53:12.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们不形成像头发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They don't make stuff like hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.08,0:53:15.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,骨头或者肌肉一样的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cartilage or muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.05,0:53:19.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是它们控制形成这些物质的基因的活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they turn on and off the genes that do.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.06,0:53:24.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔开关是DNA很有威力的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARR0LL: Switches are very powerful parts of DNA,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.93,0:53:27.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为它们允许动物在某些地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they allow animals to use genes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.93,0:53:29.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,使用基因而在其他地方则不用，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in one place and not another,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.00,0:53:33.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,在某个特定的时间点而不是其他时间点发挥作用，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at one time and not another.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.11,0:53:35.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,形成翅斑，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so,choreograph the spots
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.94,0:53:39.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,长出条纹和疹斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and stripes and blotches of animal bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.11,0:53:42.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,在果蝇这个例子里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: In the case of the fruit fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.05,0:53:43.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个基因突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's a mutation--
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.92,0:53:46.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个在DNA里极少的几个碱基的改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a change in just a few letters of the DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.05,0:53:50.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使得翅斑基因的开关打开了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has caused the paintbrush gene to be switched on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.93,0:53:56.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此，一个带有翅斑的全新物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ang so,a whole new species with wing spots
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.13,0:53:59.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,诞生了.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been created.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.06,0:54:03.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,而如今，基因开关能解释的远远不止这些.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But switches are now explaining far more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.17,0:54:06.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们帮助解决了很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are helping to solve many
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.94,0:54:10.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,复杂的基因突变的难题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perplexing evolutionary questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.04,0:54:13.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像一个物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like how one creature
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.08,0:54:17.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,失去了脚之后，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can become another creature
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.02,0:54:20.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,就变成了另外的物种.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by losing it legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.09,0:54:28.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一切都回到了达尔文在蛇的胚胎里所发现的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It all goes back to what Darwin had seen in the snake embryo.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.20,0:54:36.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,腿的雏形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rudiments of leg bumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.20,0:54:41.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,使他相信蛇肯定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This convinced him that a snake must have evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.97,0:54:45.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,是从一些四脚动物基因突变而形成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from some four-legged animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.14,0:54:48.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,在这么多年以后 同样的谜题又被解决\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the years that same mysterious process,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.18,0:54:52.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,脚消失的现象同样在其他的生物上看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the losing of legs,has been seen in other creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.99,0:54:57.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如说，鲸鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like the whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.22,0:54:59.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,它的前鳍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its front flippers have all the bones
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.99,0:55:02.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,拥有陆地动物的手臂所拥有的所有骨骼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a land creature's arm'
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.23,0:55:06.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,甚至连手指也有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even the fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.13,0:55:10.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是其躯体，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And further back in its body...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.14,0:55:14.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,也有盆骨的痕迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...it has the vestiges of a pelvis.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.21,0:55:18.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,很显然 它来源于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Clearly,it is descended
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.04,0:55:20.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,陆地上的某种爬行动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from an animal that walked on the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.18,0:55:21.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,金斯利：有些动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}KINGSLEY: Lots of animals
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.11,0:55:25.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,进化成像蛇那样在陆地上滑行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have evolved to slither through the ground like snakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.08,0:55:28.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,而有些动物则进化成像鲸鱼那样在水中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other animals slither or swim through the water
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.15,0:55:29.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,滑行或游动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.05,0:55:31.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 如果想要一副流线型的躯干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you need a streamlined body,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.26,0:55:33.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,最好除去那些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's good to get rid of these things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.23,0:55:37.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,伸出躯干的部分 比如四肢等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that stick out from the body,like limbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.23,0:55:39.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,正如鲸鱼一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Like the whale,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.20,0:55:43.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,海牛是生活在海里的另一种巨型哺乳动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the manatee is another huge mammal that lives in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.00,0:55:49.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,同样地 它们的后腿也消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it,too,has lost its hind legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.14,0:55:54.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,怎样消失的呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.02,0:56:02.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文永远无法回答这个问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin could never have answered that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.09,0:56:04.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,而如今\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now,thanks to our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.26,0:56:07.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,有了对DNA开启和关闭的了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of how DNA is switched on and off,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.26,0:56:10.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,加上那条小刺鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a very small fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.13,0:56:14.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们正慢慢接近答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we are getting a little closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.07,0:56:16.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,这片湖 位于不列颠哥伦比亚省\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this lake in British Columbia,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.27,0:56:20.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,有种生物本不应存在于此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is a creature that really shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.31,0:56:25.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,它  就是刺鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A stickleback.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.28,0:56:30.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,绝大多数刺鱼生活在海洋中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most sticklebacks live in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.15,0:56:33.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 大约1万年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But some 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.12,0:56:36.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,一些刺鱼搁浅于此湖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a few were left stranded in this lake,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.19,0:56:40.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,从此与太平洋隔绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cut off from the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.29,0:56:45.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移 他们已经进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And over the years,they have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.17,0:56:56.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,在海刺鱼的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ocean stickleback
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.24,0:56:58.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,肚皮上 有一双长得像长钉的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has a pair of fins on its belly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.31,0:57:02.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,鱼鳍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are like spikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.08,0:57:04.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是起防御保护作用的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are for defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.32,0:57:08.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们长着这长钉一样的东西 吃起来可不容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spikes make the stickleback hard to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.24,0:57:30.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 湖刺鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the lake sticklebacks
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.18,0:57:34.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,肚皮上的鱼鳍却已经消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have lost those spikes on their bellies.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.15,0:57:41.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,正是这个 引起了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's this that intrigues researchers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.35,0:57:45.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究员大卫.金斯利和他同事多尔夫的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}David Kingsley and his colleague,Dolph Schluter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.26,0:57:51.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了揭开背后的秘密 他们首先找到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To understand what's behind it,they first identified
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.10,0:57:53.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定鱼鳍的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gene that makes the stickleback's spikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.37,0:57:57.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是躯体关键基因中的一种 不出意外地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one of those key body plan genes and,not surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.37,0:58:00.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们发现海刺鱼和湖刺鱼体内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they found it to be identical in both
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.24,0:58:03.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,的这种基因别无二致\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the ocean and the lake stickleback.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.31,0:58:06.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,问题在于 为何这种基因在没有鱼鳍的湖刺鱼上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The question was,why hadn't in been turned on
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.35,0:58:10.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,并未被启动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the lake stickleback,which had lost its spikes?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.38,0:58:14.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,金斯利隐隐觉得答案就藏在基因开关中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Kingsley felt the answer might lie in a switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.39,0:58:17.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,金斯利：我们知道存在这些基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}KINGSLEY: We know these genetic switches exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.16,0:58:19.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,但仍然很难找到他们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they're still very hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.19,0:58:21.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们并没有所谓的基因密码\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't have a genetic code
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.36,0:58:23.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,能让我们顺着DNA序列读着读着说，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that lets us read along the DNA sequence and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.40,0:58:26.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿有个基因开关  然后在这个特定的地方启动基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a switch,to turn a gene on in a particular place.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.30,0:58:30.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,终于 在并不编码成蛋白质的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But eventually,hunting through the vast stretch of DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.17,0:58:34.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,茫茫DNA中 他发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that does not code for proteins,he found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.34,0:58:38.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,湖刺鱼中的一个DNA序列已经突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A section of DNA that had mutated in the lake stickleback.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.14,0:58:42.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些突变意味着 基因开关已经被破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These mutations meant that the switch was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.31,0:58:46.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,能产生鱼鳍的基因并未被启动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It didn't turn on the gene that makes spikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.16,0:58:54.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,这项工作的意义可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this work may have implications
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.33,0:58:56.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,不仅仅限于刺鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far beyond sticklebacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.29,0:58:58.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are convinced that there is a link
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.43,0:59:01.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,刺鱼鱼鳍的消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the stickleback losing its spikes
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.23,0:59:04.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,和海牛等其它生物腿的消失之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other creatures,like a manatee,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.37,0:59:06.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,存在着某种关联\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}losing their legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.44,0:59:10.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,有两条诱人的线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they have two tantalizing clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.18,0:59:13.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,第一条线索是 决定刺鱼鱼鳍的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One--the same body plan gene
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.18,0:59:15.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,关键躯体基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is responsible for the stickleback spikes,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.48,0:59:19.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,在后肢的进化中也扮演者同样的角色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also plays a role in the development of the hind limbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.19,0:59:26.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,第二条线索则不如说是假说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The second clue is more tentative.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.43,0:59:29.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,湖刺鱼的鱼鳍消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lake stickleback may have lost its spikes,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.36,0:59:33.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这一进化过程却留下了蛛丝马迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but evolution has left behind some tiny remnants...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.43,0:59:39.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,鱼刺的痕迹 随着进化 他们开始变得畸形，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the traces of bones,and they are lopsided--
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.44,0:59:43.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,左侧逐渐比右侧大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bigger on the left than on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.34,0:59:45.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,金斯利：我们想过 事实上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}KINGSLEY: We thought,Wouldn't it be amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.51,0:59:49.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果在不同动物体内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if in fact this classic unevenness is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.45,0:59:52.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,相同的控制后肢消失的基因造成了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the signature of using the same gene
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.45,0:59:56.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种典型的不对称的话 这得多么令人惊奇啊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to control hind limb loss in an incredibly different animal?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.26,1:00:05.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 金斯利和他的团队开始研究海牛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So Kingsley and his team went looking in manatees,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.30,1:00:09.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,试图探寻这种畸形现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}searching for this lopsided pattern.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.47,1:00:12.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,最终 他们有所发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they found it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.54,1:00:16.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们研究了整盒整盒的海牛骨架\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In box after box of manatee skeletons,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.24,1:00:16.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,发现海牛盆骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they saw pelvic bones
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.51,1:00:20.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,左侧大 而右侧小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that were bigger on the left and smaller on the right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.31,1:00:25.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,目前 金斯利及他的团队正尝试\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right now,Kingsley and his team are looking
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.28,1:00:26.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,从海牛体内寻找\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the same switch in the manatee
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.45,1:00:30.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,类似刺鱼体内引起鱼鳍消失的基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that caused the lake stickleback to lose its spikes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.26,1:00:33.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们找到了 这无疑将对解决那个困扰达尔文的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if they find it,they will have a powerful explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.39,1:00:35.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,提供巨大帮助\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for something that baffled Darwin--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.43,1:00:39.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个问题就是 为什么像海牛 鲸鱼和蛇等生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how creatures like manatees,whales and snakes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.36,1:00:43.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,能进化至双腿消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can evolve away their legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.30,1:00:46.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 这又引出另一个问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But all this begs another question:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.34,1:00:48.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,既然这些基因开关在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If switches can play such a profound role
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.54,1:00:51.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同动物的不同形态中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the different shapes and patterns of animal bodies--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.51,1:00:55.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如翼斑 鱼鳍和后肢等发挥这至关重要的角色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from wing spots,to spikes to hind legs--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.31,1:01:00.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,那一开始触动基因开关的又是什么呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what is throwing those switches in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.42,1:01:08.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,就像达尔文那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Researchers would see the answer in animals
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.36,1:01:12.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究员们从加拉帕哥斯群岛中的地雀找到了答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very familiar to Darwin-- those Galapagos finches.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.37,1:01:19.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,Arkat和塔宾曾经花费很长时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Arkat Abzhanov and Cliff Tabin have spent years trying
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.40,1:01:23.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,试图研究为何加拉帕哥斯的地雀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to find out exactly how those Galapagos finches
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.34,1:01:24.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,都有着不同的鸟喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}got their different beaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.44,1:01:28.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文理论告诉他们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their starting point was what they had learned
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.45,1:01:31.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,鸟喙对鸟的生存至关重要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from Darwin himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.42,1:01:34.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们从这点出发开始研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their beaks were vital to the birds' survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.55,1:01:37.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,在某个小岛上 地雀的主要食物是种子类果实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On an island where the main food was seeds,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.42,1:01:41.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们的鸟喙长得短而硬 方便敲碎果实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}finches had short,tough beaks for cracking them open.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.49,1:01:45.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,而在另外一个小岛上 主要食物是花果类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On an island where the main food was from flowers,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.43,1:01:49.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿的地雀都长着长长的尖嘴 以便吮吸花蜜和花粉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}birds had long pointy beaks for sunking up nectar and pollen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.47,1:01:56.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时 他们另有发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they knew something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.51,1:02:00.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,雀鸟出生时 他们的嘴已经完全成形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The finches are born with their beaks fully formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.58,1:02:02.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 鸟喙形状各异的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the answer to why they had
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.58,1:02:05.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,必定是在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such different beaks must lie in something
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.48,1:02:09.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,当雀鸟还在胚胎即鸟蛋中的时候 发生了什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that happened te them as embryos in the egg.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.52,1:02:11.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾：鸟蛋中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}TABIN: Something amazing
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.46,1:02:12.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,正上演神奇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is happening inside those eggs.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.49,1:02:14.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同的基因正或开启 或关闭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Genes are turning on and turning off.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.59,1:02:18.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,而如何开启或关闭将决定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And depending on exactly how they turn on and off
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.56,1:02:22.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,将决定形成哪种雀鸟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will determine what type of finch is formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.37,1:02:26.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了弄明刚刚发生的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: To find out just what was going on,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.40,1:02:30.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究专家们首先得收集些鸟蛋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the researchers first had to collect some eggs.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.44,1:02:32.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,悄悄地说 在这儿呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(whispers): There she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.54,1:02:35.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,她刚回来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She just came back. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.51,1:02:36.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,准备下蛋呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To lay eggs.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.51,1:02:40.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,看起来她得下好几个呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's really likely that she already has a clutch; great.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.49,1:02:41.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,要出来了...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She's coming out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.59,1:02:45.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,看了下地雀鸟巢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Abzhanov checks a ground finch nest
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.42,1:02:47.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,只发现一直鸟蛋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and finds a single egg.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.43,1:02:48.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,他不能拿走这独个鸟蛋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He won't remove it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.49,1:02:52.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为鸟妈妈很可能会因此放弃这个鸟巢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the mother might abandon the nest.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.47,1:02:56.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外一个鸟巢已经生了三个鸟蛋了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another nest already has three eggs.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.40,1:02:58.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,他拿走其中一个用来研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He takes one for his research,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.40,1:03:02.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,他知道 鸟妈妈会再下一个鸟蛋替代拿走的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as he knows the mother will lay a replacement.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.51,1:03:05.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,研究团队收集了好些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The team collects several eggs,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.51,1:03:09.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同胚胎时期的鸟蛋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with embryos at different stages of development.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.38,1:03:11.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样 他们就能清晰地画出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That way they will be able to chart exactly
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.55,1:03:15.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同鸟喙的发育过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how the different beaks grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.59,1:03:20.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,回到实验中 他们已经能够开始了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in the lab,they can begin the process.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.53,1:03:27.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个仙人掌雀胚胎正很好地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This cactus finch embryo is well on the way
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.63,1:03:31.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,发育着它那标志性的又长又尖的喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to its signature long,pointy beak.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.40,1:03:35.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这只地雀胚胎也正发着它那又短又厚的喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this ground finch embryo is growing a short,thick beak.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.41,1:03:39.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们想弄明白这些进化的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we wanted to do was try and understand the genes
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.54,1:03:42.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,是怎么改变鸟喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that were involved in making the beak the way it was--
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.58,1:03:45.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,变成成又大又厚的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making a big,broad thick beak different
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.45,1:03:47.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,而不是长而薄或者短而薄的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a long,thin beak or a short,thin beak.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.55,1:03:50.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们曾集中精力研究一组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: They concentrated on a group of genes
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.66,1:03:54.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定鸟类面部生长的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known to control the growth of birds' faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.46,1:03:59.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们观察发现了一些有趣的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As they looked,they saw something intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.47,1:04:05.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个特定的躯体控制基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One particular body plan gene
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.67,1:04:07.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,于第五天在长短厚鸟喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}became active in the ground finch
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.54,1:04:11.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,的地雀体内变得活跃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the short,thick beak,on the fifth day of development.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.58,1:04:13.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而又过了24小时 这个基因却还是未能在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it didn't go to work in the cactus finch
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.75,1:04:17.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,长着细长鸟喙的体内发生作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with its long,slender beak for another 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.68,1:04:22.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,这给了我们启迪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.49,1:04:25.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,在所有种类的鸟雀中 相同的基因决定着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same genes were responsible for the beaks
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.52,1:04:27.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,不一样的鸟喙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in all types of finch.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.56,1:04:30.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这些差异是由于 基因开启 时机和强度的不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Any differences were in timing and intensity.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.66,1:04:32.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾：我们搞明白了 我们彻底清楚了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}TABIN: We've got it! We nailed it!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.60,1:04:36.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,相同的基因决定着鸟喙的不同 或尖利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the same genes in making a sharp,pointy beak
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.60,1:04:38.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,或宽大 能啄碎坚果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or a big,broad nut-cracking beak.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.57,1:04:41.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,而造成这些差异的关键在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's essential,what makes the difference,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.51,1:04:44.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,你多大程度地开启了基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all the difference,is how much you turn the gene on,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.61,1:04:48.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,又是何时开启或关闭它的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you turn it on,when you turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.51,1:04:51.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一发现带给我们的启示远非这些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And the revelations didn't end there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.55,1:04:54.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一基因有些特殊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was something special about this gene.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.55,1:04:57.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,和所有的躯体控制基因并不会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like all body plan genes,it doesn't actually
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.66,1:04:59.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,变成我们躯体的某部分那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make the stuff of our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.76,1:05:03.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一基因也没有变成这些鸟雀嘴巴的软骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It didn't make the cartilage for the finches' beaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.76,1:05:06.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,它只是启动基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It throws switches.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.77,1:05:10.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因开关随后开启或关闭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the switches then turn on or off the genes
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.64,1:05:13.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些形成鸟喙的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that do make the beak.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.71,1:05:15.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：这些是不同类型的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: These are a different type of gene.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.77,1:05:19.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们控制着其他基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're genes that boss other genes around.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.51,1:05:24.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们现在意识到 并非所有的基因都生而平等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists now realize that not all genes are created equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.72,1:05:27.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,一些基因成为我们躯体的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some make the stuff of our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.75,1:05:28.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这就需要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And switches are needed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.75,1:05:32.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,基因开关来开启或关闭这些所谓的 组织 基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to turn many of these "stuff" genes on and off.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.59,1:05:35.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,正是躯体控制基因开启了这些基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The body plan genes are what throw these switches,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.76,1:05:39.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定着 组织 基因何时做何事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which tell the stuff genes what to do and when.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.60,1:05:43.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些微妙的安排将对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This subtle choreography can have profound effects
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.67,1:05:47.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同动物躯体的形成产生深刻的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on how different animal bodies are formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.57,1:05:50.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一知识正帮我们解答\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this knowledge is helping us solve
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.71,1:05:53.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,或许是达尔文之谜中最难的谜题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps the biggest Darwinian puzzle of all:
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.78,1:05:57.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的变化之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mystery of the great transformations.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.75,1:06:06.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,这一切得追溯到达尔文对生命之树的看法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It all goes back to Darwin's idea of the tree of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.79,1:06:11.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,他认为 所有的生命形式最终都是互相关联的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That all life-forms are ultimately related.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.63,1:06:15.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,源自最初的共同祖先 经过数十亿年之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And from the earliest common ancestor over billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.83,1:06:17.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们发生着改变 并呈现出多样性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they have changed and diversified
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.87,1:06:21.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 所有的生物都从最初的看似相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that creatures that started out looking the same
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.61,1:06:25.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,逐渐进化成了后来的完全不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}evolved to become completely different.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.61,1:06:32.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们发现了很多令人惊异的关联\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And scientists have made some amazing connections.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.89,1:06:37.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如恐龙和鸟类拥有相同的祖先\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That dinosaurs share a common ancestor with birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.72,1:06:42.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,再比如鱼类很可能是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that a fish must have been the ancestor
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.69,1:06:46.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,所有四肢动物的祖先 甚至包括人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of all four-limbed creatures--even us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.67,1:06:52.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文的所有观点中 这个可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all his ideas,this was probably
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.60,1:06:56.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,是其中最惊人的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin's most astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.67,1:06:57.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：搞清楚 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: It was one thing to grasp
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.78,1:06:59.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,两种鸟雀为何不同和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how two species of finch could become different,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.88,1:07:02.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们的鸟喙是怎么变化的是一回事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how their beak shape could change.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.71,1:07:03.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,这只是一小步而已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was a small step.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.75,1:07:04.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 那些巨大的差异呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what about the big differences?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.82,1:07:07.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如游于海中的鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The differences,say,between the fish that swim in the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.82,1:07:09.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,和行于陆地的动物呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the animals that walk on land?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.72,1:07:12.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些差异又是如何发生的呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did those changes take place?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.66,1:07:14.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,多年来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Over the years,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.63,1:07:18.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,发生这些巨大差异的证据已被找到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}evidence for these great transformations has been found.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.80,1:07:22.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如说 达尔文发表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For instance,just a year after Darwin published
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.63,1:07:23.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,《物种起源》仅仅一年以后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the Origin of Species,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.87,1:07:27.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,一种被称为“始祖鸟”的化石被发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a fossil called "archaeopteryx" was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.87,1:07:32.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,上面有着鸟和恐龙的特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It had features of both birds and dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.91,1:07:38.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文在胚胎中找到了同样有说服力的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Darwin had seen equally persuasive evidence in embryos.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.89,1:07:44.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,在所有陆地生物甚至包括人类中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those slits in the ear of all land creatures,even humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.76,1:07:49.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些耳朵中的狭缝在人类中变成内耳中的幼骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In us,they become tiny bones in the inner ear.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.87,1:07:57.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,而在鱼类中 他们则变成鱼鳃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in fish,they become gills.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.77,1:08:01.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,这暗示着陆地动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A tantalizing hint that land animals
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.64,1:08:04.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,都是鱼的后裔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}must be descended from fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.68,1:08:08.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 鱼是如何长出肢干并能在陆地上行走这一问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the stumbling block has always been how.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.85,1:08:12.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,一直阻碍着我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could a fish develop legs and walk on land?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.66,1:08:23.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文毫无头绪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Darwin had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.80,1:08:33.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,而舒本决定啃这块硬骨头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Neil Shubin was determined to tackle that problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.71,1:08:35.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：这让我浮想联翩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: It captured my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.71,1:08:38.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,看 这是鱼翅 而另一方面则是肢干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean,here's a fin and on the other side was a limb.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.78,1:08:40.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们看起来是如此地不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they looked different in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.81,1:08:44.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就想 这真是个值得我全身心投入的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I thought,"Well,what a first-class scientific problem
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.75,1:08:46.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学难题之最\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to devote my research to."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.72,1:08:47.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 我已经致力于此项研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I've been devoting pretty much
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.92,1:08:51.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,超过20年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}my research to it ever since,over 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.92,1:08:55.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本研究的第一步是找到一颗化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRTTOR: The hrst stage Shubin's quest was to find a fossil.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.83,1:09:00.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果从某种意义上说 达尔文是正确的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If Darwin were right,somewhere out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.87,1:09:02.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么一定有个过渡形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there had to be a transitional form,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.87,1:09:06.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,一颗拥有肢干雏形的鱼化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a fossil that was part fish,but had the beginning of legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.84,1:09:12.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,但问题是 去哪儿找呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where to look?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.71,1:09:15.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他想到了一个办法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had one clue.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.75,1:09:18.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,化石记录表明 有腿生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fossil record shows that creatures with legs
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.75,1:09:22.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,首先出现于大约3亿6500万年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first appeared some 365 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.72,1:09:27.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,而在那之前 只有鱼类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before that,they were only fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.83,1:09:35.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 年复一年 舒本\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So,summer after summer,Shubin set up camp
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.80,1:09:38.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,在离北极仅有几百英里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on Ellesmere Island,just a few hundred miles
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.94,1:09:39.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,埃尔斯米尔岛上安营扎寨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.87,1:09:43.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿散落着这一关键过渡时期的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has exposed rock from that crucial transitional time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.88,1:09:46.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,从科学家们拍的视频可以看出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The scientist's own video shows
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.81,1:09:50.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿是多么地偏远 多么地荒凉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how remote and bleak the place was.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.78,1:09:51.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：这儿天气寒冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.78,1:09:54.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,整个夏天几乎都结冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's about freezing every day over the summer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.89,1:09:55.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,风很猛烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Winds are high.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.89,1:09:57.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,风速可以达到50英里每小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can get up to 50 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.89,1:09:59.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿还有北极熊出没\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are polar bears there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.02,1:10:01.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们不得不携带者枪支防身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have to prepare ourselves by carrying guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.83,1:10:03.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是个美丽的地方 你必须得爱她\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a beautiful place. You've got to love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.83,1:10:06.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,这儿是我的夏日之家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's my summer home.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.93,1:10:10.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,每一次远征的代价都及其高昂 三次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NAREATOR: Each expedition was costly,but after three of them
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.90,1:10:13.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,就足以证明他们的决心有多大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there was little to show for their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.91,1:10:17.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此第四次远征就显得毫无意义了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A fourth trip seemed pointless.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.01,1:10:22.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：我记得跟我同事的一次谈话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: I remember having a conversation with my colleagues saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.05,1:10:26.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,你说 我们真的该去吗 花费真的很高吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well,should we go? Is this really a waste of money?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:29.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一次至关重要的时刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was our do-or-die moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.79,1:10:33.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们几乎没去成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we almost didn't go.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.06,1:10:37.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们决定再去最后一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But they decided to try one last time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.90,1:10:46.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,三天以后 他们依然一无所获\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After three days,they still hadn't found anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.84,1:10:53.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后 当大家都心灰意冷时...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then,just when no one was expecting anything to happen...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.05,1:10:57.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一名同事正在敲石头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A colleague was cracking rocks
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.82,1:10:59.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,那时我正离他五英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and I was working about five feet from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.85,1:11:03.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后 我听到 嘿 嘿 伙计们 这是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I hear,"Hey! Hey,guys,what's this?"
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.99,1:11:12.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,探出石头外面的是个鱼头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sticking out of the cliff was the snout of fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.06,1:11:16.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可不是一般的鱼 这可是条平头鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And not just any fish,a fish with a flat head.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.87,1:11:18.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,看到这条\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By seeing a flat-headed fish
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.07,1:11:22.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,大约3亿7500万年前岩石中的平头鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in rocks about 375 million years old...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.01,1:11:26.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们都意识到终于找到了我们一直想要的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we knew we had found what we were looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.91,1:11:31.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,一只扁平的鱼头 眼睛向上凝视着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: A flat snout with upward staring eyes--
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.92,1:11:33.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,它拼命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the signature of an animal
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.02,1:11:34.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,想把头探出水面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that pushes its head out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.99,1:11:38.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 它需要借助其它东西比如四肢来探出水面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And for that,it would have needed something like arms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.99,1:11:43.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：我们顿时蹦蹦跳跳 互相击掌庆祝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: What we did at that moment was all jump around high-fiving.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.86,1:11:45.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,那时 整个现场只有我们六个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was,uh,you know,there were only six of us
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.13,1:11:49.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,场面很壮观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the field that time,so it was quite a scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.07,1:11:55.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,回来后 舒本和他的团队继续工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Back at home,Shubin and his team got to work,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.04,1:11:59.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,开始化验那颗拥有3亿7500万年历史的化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}examining their 375-million-year-old fossil.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.08,1:12:05.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们把这个新发现的鱼叫做“提克塔利”鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They named their new finding "Tiktaalik,"
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.95,1:12:09.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,这在因纽特语中指淡水鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an Inuit word for a freshwater fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.96,1:12:14.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,提克塔利鱼是个完美的过渡产物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tiktaalik is a perfect transitional form.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.93,1:12:17.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,它大部分长得像鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much of its body is that of a fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.13,1:12:21.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,有鱼鳞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's covered in scales.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.07,1:12:25.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,但同时它也有些非鱼的特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it also had something very un-fishlike...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.94,1:12:33.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如它长着手臂状的鱼鳍 或者说鱼鳍状的手臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an arm-like fin,or perhaps a fin-like arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.02,1:12:41.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,提克塔利鱼有着所有四肢动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tiktaalik had the bone structure that is seen
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.95,1:12:45.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,所拥有的骨骼结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the arms and legs of every four-limbed animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.06,1:12:49.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,上面有块骨头 比较大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One big bone at the top,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.06,1:12:50.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,下面有两块骨头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}two bones underneath,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.19,1:12:54.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使得腕部和踝部有一些骨头群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leading to a cluster of bones in the wrist and ankle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.04,1:13:00.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些所有的生物从\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the same pattern that is found in everything
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.10,1:13:04.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,羊到牧羊犬 甚至到舒本本身 都有着同样的结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from sheep,to sheepdogs,to Shubin himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.04,1:13:07.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们找到了一种动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You now have an animal
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.11,1:13:09.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,它能从底部冒出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can push itself up off the substrate,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.95,1:13:13.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,不管是在水底 还是陆地上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}either on the water bottom or on land.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.99,1:13:18.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,问题显而易见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: One obvious question was:
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.12,1:13:22.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,为何提克塔利进化成这样的新结构呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why had Tiktaalik evolved this new structure?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.13,1:13:29.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,就在它附近发现的另外一颗化石可能能回答这一问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One possible answer is suggested by other fossils found near it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.17,1:13:34.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些大型捕食性鱼类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are large predatory fish
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.04,1:13:38.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,大约10至15英尺长 和提克塔利鱼生活在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about ten to 15 feet long living alongside Tiktaalik.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.11,1:13:42.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,提克塔利鱼成为了猎物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Tiktaalik was prey.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.98,1:13:46.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,为了生存下去 它们没多少选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To survive,it had few choices.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.12,1:13:52.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,要么长得大一点 要么长得坚硬一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can get big,you can get armor
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.02,1:13:55.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,或者 要么选择离开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or you can get out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.03,1:13:58.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本 认为提克塔利鱼选择了离开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Shubin thinks Tiktaalik got out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.10,1:14:03.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,用那些臂状的鱼鳍它们拼命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With those arm-like fins,it could have dragged itself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.97,1:14:07.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,往陆地或浅滩逃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to safety on land or in the shallows.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.24,1:14:14.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,但这仅仅解释了问题的一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this was only half the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.05,1:14:18.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,这并未揭示基因的真正机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What it doesn't show us is the actual genetic mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.98,1:14:21.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,即如何把决定鱼鳍的基因变成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the genetic recipe that builds a fin
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.25,1:14:25.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定肢干的基因的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into that which builds a limb.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.03,1:14:33.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,经历了3亿7500万年之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: At 375 million years old,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.13,1:14:37.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,提克塔利鱼的DNA早已消失不见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tiktaalik's DNA had vanished long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.27,1:14:39.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 舒本需要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shubin needed a next-of-kin,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.20,1:14:43.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,另外和鱼相关的仍存活的同类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a fish relative that was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.04,1:14:47.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：我们需要的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: What we needed was a creature
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.14,1:14:50.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,在进化树中处于正确位置的一种生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was in the right part of the evolutionary tree,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.11,1:14:54.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,它得是拥有非常肉质鱼鳍的鱼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but also a fish that has a very fleshy fin.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.05,1:14:58.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,于是 他们继续搜寻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the search was on.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.09,1:15:02.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,有好几种鱼符合条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: A number of fish fit the bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.23,1:15:06.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,而 舒宾 唯独选择了一种...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Shubin favored one in particular...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.10,1:15:11.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,白鲟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the paddlefish.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.07,1:15:13.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：白鲟可谓是非常奇怪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: The paddlefish is a really weird fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.27,1:15:16.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们已经长出了很长的鼻子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They developed this really long snout.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.07,1:15:17.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,并且非常贪食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're really voracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.31,1:15:18.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们甚至相食对方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They eat each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.21,1:15:20.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 当他们游在一起的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So oftentimes you'll lose a lot of your fish
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.14,1:15:24.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,你会发现逐渐少了一些 因为他们互相吞掉对方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when they swim together,because they'll eat each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.18,1:15:27.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,密西西比河的浅滩中的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Living in the shallow waters of the Mississippi,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.32,1:15:31.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,真可称得上是活化石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's also a living fossil.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.12,1:15:35.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们花了好些年 试图弄清\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have spent years working out the relationships
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.19,1:15:37.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,不同鱼类之间的关系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between different species of fish
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.29,1:15:39.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们发现白鲟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they know that the paddlefish
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.23,1:15:40.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,是和提克塔利鱼属于同种鱼类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is one of the last survivors
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.30,1:15:44.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,的仅有幸存者之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the class to which Tiktaalik once belonged.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.37,1:15:46.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 不像提克塔利鱼那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But unlike Tiktaalik,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.20,1:15:49.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,白鲟数量众多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the paddlefish is in plentiful supply.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.21,1:15:51.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,白鲟是鱼子酱的一种常见来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Paddlefish is a common source for caviar.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.34,1:15:55.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此我们通常从鱼子酱农场得到白鲟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we'd get our paddlefish from caviar farms.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.28,1:16:00.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,有趣的是 虽然提克塔利鱼濒临灭绝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Intriguingly,even though Tiktaalik is extinct,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.22,1:16:05.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,但实际上白鲟才是更原始的种族\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the paddlefish is actually the more primitive form.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.12,1:16:06.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟提克塔利鱼比起来 白鲟的鱼鳍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its fins bear far less relation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.32,1:16:10.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,与臂或者腿关系不如那么密切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to an arm or leg than Tiktaalik's .
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.23,1:16:12.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,由于白鲟和提克塔利鱼息息相关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And because they are related,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.13,1:16:16.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,这两种鱼应该拥有相同的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the two kinds of fish should share the same genes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.34,1:16:24.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,于是，舒本开始研究白鲟胚胎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So Shubin began looking at paddlefish embryos,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.31,1:16:28.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,试图找寻决定鱼鳍的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hunting for the genes that built its fins.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.35,1:16:34.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,很快 他锁定了一组特定的名为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And soon he zeroed in on one particular group
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.42,1:16:38.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,Hox的基因组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of body plan genes called Hox genes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.26,1:16:48.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,几乎在所有的稍微复杂的动物中 都能找到Hox基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hox genes have been found in all complex animals
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.23,1:16:52.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,从大约6亿年前的天鹅绒虫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the velvet worm,that dates back some 600 million years,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.14,1:16:57.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,到现代人类 都可以找到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the modern human.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.24,1:17:01.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,并且从始至终 他们的DNA序列\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in all that time,the letters of their DNA
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.18,1:17:04.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,都几乎保持不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have remained virtually unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.18,1:17:07.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们是基因群中的贵族\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are aristocrats of the gene community,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.38,1:17:10.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,非常接近权利链的顶端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near the very top of the chain of command.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.42,1:17:14.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们通过发育中的胚胎发号施令\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They give orders that cascade through a developing embryo...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.39,1:17:20.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,能激活发育成躯体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}activating entire networks of switches and genes
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.27,1:17:25.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,整个基因开关网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that make the parts of the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.21,1:17:31.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们对生物的发育起着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are absolutely critical to the shape and form
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.48,1:17:33.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,至关重要的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a developing creature.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.34,1:17:35.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：这些基因决定着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: These genes determine where the front
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.21,1:17:37.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,动物的前部和后部长成什么样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the back et the animal's going te be--
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.31,1:17:39.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,顶部 底部 左边 右边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the top,the bottom,the left,right,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.32,1:17:41.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,内部 外部分别长成如何 眼睛该长在何处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the inside,the outside-where the eyes are going to be,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.39,1:17:44.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,腿该长在哪里 肠道又该长在哪里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the legs are going to be,where the gut's going to be--
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.42,1:17:46.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,能长几个手指\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how many fingers they're going to have.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.26,1:17:50.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本发现 Hox基因在白鲟鳍的形成过程中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Shubin found that Hox genes had a key role
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.26,1:17:56.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,起着关键的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the formation of paddlefish fins.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.30,1:18:01.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一组Hox基因控制着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One set of Hox genes orders
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.21,1:18:03.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,鱼鳍发育的第一阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the first stage of fin development--
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.24,1:18:07.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,这期间 白鲟躯干长出了一块坚硬的软骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a sturdy piece of cartilage that grows out from the torso.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.21,1:18:14.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,令人惊讶的是 在所有的包括人类的所有四肢动物中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Amazingly,in all four-limbed animals,even us.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.19,1:18:19.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,完全相同的基因决定着长长的上臂骨的生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Exactly the same genes create the long upper arm bone.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.40,1:18:27.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,在白鲟中 另一Hox基因组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the paddlefish,another set of Hox genes
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.30,1:18:31.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,控制鱼鳍生长的下一阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}command the next stage of fin development.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.40,1:18:34.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,同样地 又是完全一样的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Again,exactly the same genes
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.24,1:18:38.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,控制我们前臂骨骼的生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}control the growth of our two forearm bones.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.25,1:18:47.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,最终 相同的基因以不同的顺序\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finally,the same genes,working in a different order,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.42,1:18:51.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,决定着鱼鳍的末端骨头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make the array of bones at the end of the fin.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.42,1:18:55.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,而又是相同的基因以同样的顺序\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same sequence of the same genes
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.26,1:18:59.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,组成了我们手指和脚趾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}makes our fingers and toes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.36,1:19:04.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可是个重大发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was a massive revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.31,1:19:11.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,瞬间地 所有有肢动物的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Suddenly the origin of creatures with arms and legs
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.51,1:19:15.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,看起来似乎并不存在巨大差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}didn't seem such a huge leap after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.35,1:19:19.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果提克塔利鱼中也存在同样基因发挥作用的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It the same genes were at work in Tiktaalik,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.28,1:19:23.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么史前鱼类就应该已经携带了好些能控制肢干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then many of the genes needed to make legs and arms
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.39,1:19:28.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,生长的这些基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were already being carried around by prehistoric fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.30,1:19:35.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,只需要几次突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All it needed was a few mutations--
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.33,1:19:39.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,关于基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a few changes to the timing and order
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.37,1:19:42.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,何时开关的突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what was turned off and on,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.44,1:19:44.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,鱼鳍便能变成肢干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a fin could become a limb.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.51,1:19:48.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,舒本：通常情况下 进化过程中 基因全新结构的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SHUBIN: Oftentimes the origin of whole new structures in evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.41,1:19:51.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,并不涉及新基因的来源或\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}doesn't involve the origin of new genes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.28,1:19:51.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,整个全新基因图谱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or whole new genetic recipes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.55,1:19:55.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,那些老的基因经过重新配置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Old genes,old genetic pathways can be reconfigured
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.52,1:20:00.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,产生了全新的美妙事物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make marvelously wonderful new things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.53,1:20:14.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 现在达尔文无法解答的问题有了可能的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So it is now possible to answer what Darwin didn't know
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.44,1:20:18.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们亦能解释为何四肢动物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and explain how all four-legged creatures
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.51,1:20:22.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,很可能起源于鱼类了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could be descended from fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.42,1:20:31.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,在大约3亿7500万年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Around 375 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.36,1:20:35.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,像提克塔利鱼那类生物收到攻击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a creature like Tiktaalik was under attack...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.59,1:20:39.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,遭遇捕食者的掠杀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}harried by predators.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.37,1:20:51.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而一些Hox基因的随机变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But some random changes to the activity of the Hox genes
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.51,1:20:55.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,使得他们的鱼鳍逐渐变成肢干\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}led to its fins,developing a structure like a limb.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.45,1:21:04.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,接着 提克塔利鱼能逃离险境 成功着陆了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tiktaalik could now haul itself out of danger,onto dry land.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.63,1:21:14.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,在陆地上 它会发现一个植物丛生 昆虫遍地的世界...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On land,it would have found a world of plants and insects...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.37,1:21:23.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个等待征服的世界......\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a world ripe for colonization...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.38,1:21:28.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个属于有肢动物的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a world perfect for animals with arms and legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.52,1:21:36.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,再之后 又经过了数百万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so,over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.65,1:21:40.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们长出来的肢干继续进化 变得丰富多彩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these new limbs evolved,changed and diversified.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.63,1:21:46.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,有的奔跑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some became adapted for running.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.56,1:21:51.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,有的飞翔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others for flying.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.44,1:21:57.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,有的能挖洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some for digging.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.64,1:22:03.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,而有的会旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others for swinging.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.52,1:22:07.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,就这样 四肢动物以各种方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so four-limbed creatures took over the world
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.58,1:22:11.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,占领了这个世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a multitude of different ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.59,1:22:19.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这 都源于当初一些古老基因组的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all because of some changes to an ancient set of genes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.63,1:22:25.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,这也正是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this is the true wonder
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.57,1:22:29.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们对DNA的新认识告诉我们的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of where our new understanding of DNA has led us to.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.67,1:22:33.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,存在着组成我们躯体的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are genes that make the stuff of our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.51,1:22:36.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,也存在着控制这些基因开闭的基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}switches that turn them off and on,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.61,1:22:40.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及控制这些基因开关的其他基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and still other genes that give those switches orders.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.72,1:22:44.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,加上复杂的 基因开关开启和关闭 时机和强度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Together in a complex cascade of timing and intensity,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.52,1:22:49.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们一起产生了这个星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they combine to produce the amazing diversity
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.66,1:22:53.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,的万事万物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.67,1:22:58.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,这 真是达尔文所闻所未闻的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That truly is something that Darwin never knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.47,1:23:05.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 这一新科学能解释\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But can this new science also explain
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.51,1:23:09.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类从何处来 这个或许是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps the most fundamental question of all?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.58,1:23:14.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,最根本的问题吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What makes us human?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.59,1:23:23.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的活动范围实在是令人惊叹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The scope of human activity is simply astounding.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.53,1:23:26.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我对人类的一切疯狂行为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What fascinated me were
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.50,1:23:28.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,极其感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the crazy things that humans do.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.60,1:23:31.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You look around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.50,1:23:33.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你发现有什么奇怪或者是有趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and if there is something bizarre and interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.74,1:23:34.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,的事儿好玩儿的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you could be doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.67,1:23:38.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,说不定世界上其他地方的人类也在玩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}humans are up to it somewhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.61,1:23:41.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,当你看到这所有的一切时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when you look at all of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.61,1:23:44.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,你只需要自问一句 人类为何如此特别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you just have to ask yourself,what makes us special?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.62,1:23:48.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的本源又是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is the basis for this humanness?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.56,1:23:53.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,对于自然的所有鬼斧神工来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: For all nature's wonders,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.56,1:23:57.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类取得的成就可谓独一无二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the achievements of the human mind are truly unique.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.76,1:24:01.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们是唯一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are the only species
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.70,1:24:04.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,会思考其他物种会怎么看待人类的物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to think about what others think about us,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.70,1:24:08.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,会惩罚我们的侵害之物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to punish those who have harmed others,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.74,1:24:12.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,会创造艺术...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create art...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.71,1:24:15.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,音乐...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}music...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.65,1:24:18.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,建筑...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}architecture...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.72,1:24:21.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,从事科学研究...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to engage in science...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.75,1:24:25.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,医学研究...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}medicine...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.72,1:24:29.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,会开发微芯片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the microchip.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.70,1:24:37.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,只有我们 能举手之间摧毁数百万的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only we can destroy millions at the push of a button.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.61,1:24:46.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,毫不奇怪地 一直以来 我们都认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hardly surprising,then,that for centuries we thought
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.78,1:24:49.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类和其他一切物种都不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that humans were different from all other species,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.71,1:24:53.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们是照着神的样子所造 更为高等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}better,created in the image of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.72,1:25:01.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 后来达尔文\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then Darwin began to draw conclusions from evidence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.69,1:25:05.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,根据人类胚胎中的鳃裂得出结论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like gill slits in human embryos
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.63,1:25:09.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类起源于鱼类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that showed that we were descended from fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.60,1:25:15.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,人群惊叫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(people exclaim)
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.71,1:25:17.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,但当提到其它近亲物种时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was when he drew parallels with other
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.77,1:25:21.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文陷入了麻烦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}close relatives that he got into real trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.81,1:25:25.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,卡罗尔：达尔文结束航程返回伦敦后不久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CARROLL: Shortly after Darwin returned from his voyage,in London,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.62,1:25:27.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,一只名叫“珍妮”的猩猩开始展出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an orangutan named Jenny went on exhibit.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.68,1:25:28.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,这引起了巨大的轰动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this was a huge sensation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.79,1:25:31.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是被关着展出的第一支猩猩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was the first great ape to be exhibited in captivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.86,1:25:34.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文被这只猩猩的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Darwin was absolutely taken
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.69,1:25:37.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,童真般的天性深深吸引\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with how she was sort of childlike in her ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.73,1:25:41.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时 他发现这只猩猩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he saw a lot of human behavior
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.60,1:25:45.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,和诸多人类行为及其相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the way this orangutan behaved.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.80,1:25:47.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,达尔文认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: When Darwin suggested
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.70,1:25:51.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 人类应该是来源于类人猿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that human beings must actually be descended from apes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.61,1:25:53.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他因此遭受了猛烈抨击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he was savaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.74,1:25:55.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,他被指控为攻击当时的核心信念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was accused of attacking that core belief
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.85,1:25:59.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,即上帝创造了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that humankind had been created in the image of God
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.65,1:26:02.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,高于一切生物的人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}above all other creatures.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.65,1:26:06.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,如今 我们和类人猿祖先一样这一理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But today the idea that we share a common ancestor with apes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.63,1:26:10.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,在生物学上已被广泛接受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is completely accepted in biology.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.73,1:26:13.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 把人类和类人猿的基因组排序后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead,as a result of having sequenced the genomes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.86,1:26:17.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,麻烦来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of both humans and apes,we face a very different puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.87,1:26:21.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,凯蒂 波拉德 是黑猩猩DNA方面的专家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Katie Pollard is an expert on chimp DNA.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.91,1:26:23.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于人类和黑猩猩之间存在着明显差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Given all the obvious differences between humans
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.81,1:26:26.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,你可能会觉得两者之间的DNA应该迥异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and chimps,you might expect our DNA to be really different.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.78,1:26:30.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 事实上 两者近似度可以达到99%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in fact,it's more like 99% identical.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.89,1:26:38.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类和黑猩猩的DNA仅仅存在1%的差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Just a one-percent difference in the DNA of humans and chimps.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.86,1:26:45.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,现代科学面临的谜题并非是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mystery facing modern science is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.90,1:26:48.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,如此不同的动物间怎么可能密切相关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not how can such different animals be related,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.80,1:26:52.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是 关系如此紧密的动物会如此地不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but how can such closely related species be so different?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.94,1:26:57.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这是达尔文从来不明白的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That really is something that Darwin never knew,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.84,1:27:01.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们逐渐找到了答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but slowly,scientists are starting to find the answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.82,1:27:08.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们首先从研究人类的一个关键器官\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one answer begins with insights into the genetics
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.75,1:27:13.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,手 找到了答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a key human organ,our hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.79,1:27:19.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的手真是一大奇迹 它敏捷而灵巧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The human hand is a marvel,nimble and dexterous.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.97,1:27:26.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,大自然中从未出现过像这样的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing quite like it exists anywhere else in nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.70,1:27:29.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,手给与了我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It offers us a unique combination
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.91,1:27:31.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,精度和力量的独特组合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of precision and power,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.91,1:27:35.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这都在拇指上完美体现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and much of that is down to one particular digit,our thumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.75,1:27:43.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类的手特征之一便是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the features of the human hand is our ability
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.76,1:27:47.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们能用拇指碰触到其他四个手指\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to touch all four fingers with the thumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.86,1:27:50.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,这使得我们可以像这样抓握\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that allows us to make grips like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.76,1:27:53.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,非常好把握精确度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gives us a lot of precision.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.83,1:27:57.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,强力抓握体现了使很大劲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The power grip is the ability to put a lot of strength
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.74,1:28:00.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样抓的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into this soft of contact.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.77,1:28:04.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 你拿着球的时候 你主要是在捏它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you're holding a ball,you're basically pinching it,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.01,1:28:09.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,并可以使劲捏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can put a lot of strength into that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.01,1:28:12.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,最好抛个快球试试\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The better to throw a fastball with.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.95,1:28:18.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,以便找出跟人类最接近的物种相比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding out why we have such versatile hands
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.96,1:28:21.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,为何我们拥有如此灵巧的手\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to our nearest relatives is the task
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.89,1:28:25.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是耶鲁大学 吉姆 努南 的主要工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of Jim Noonan at Yale University.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.80,1:28:29.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,他开始筛选那人类与黑猩猩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He began sifting through that vital one percent of DNA
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.03,1:28:32.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,存在差异的1%的DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is different in humans from chimps.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.80,1:28:35.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,努南：科学上一个很基本的问题就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NOONAN: It's kind of one of the fundamental questions
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.01,1:28:38.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,是什么让我们与众不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in science is: What makes us who we are?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.98,1:28:42.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,真的 这正是我们试图弄明白的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An that's really what we're trying to get to;
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.91,1:28:45.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,是什么使得人类之所以成为人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what makes humans human.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.02,1:28:48.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一项缓慢的工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: It was slow work.
