Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.31,1:35:23.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在自己体内也找到了相同的缺陷基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he found the same damaged gene in himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.15,1:35:25.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我正研究我自己的DNA,\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm seeing this in my own DNA,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.35,1:35:27.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,这似乎表明  等等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's suggesting that Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.38,1:35:30.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,似乎我身上也有某种肌肉病\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means there's a muscle disease here somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.39,1:35:33.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是我没意识到而已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a muscle disease that I'm unaware of.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.19,1:35:35.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想或许值得检查一下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I thought it would be worth checking this out
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.39,1:35:38.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,实验室的其他同事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in some other members of the lab.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.33,1:35:42.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,几次擦拭酒精之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: A few swabs later and...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.33,1:35:45.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼：显然 那天结束之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}STEDMAN: Sure enough,at the end of the day,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.44,1:35:47.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,发现在每个人的DNA的相同位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every single person had the same glitch
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.40,1:35:51.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,都找到了相同的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in their same DNA at the same place.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.21,1:35:57.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可真是个谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Here then was a real mystery.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.21,1:36:01.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,似乎这种肌肉组成基因在人体内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seemed that this particular muscle-making gene
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.19,1:36:03.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,广泛存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was common in humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.39,1:36:07.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在类人猿中也发现了相同的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when he identified the same gene in apes,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.39,1:36:11.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,和其他肌肉组成基因一样的基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was just like any other muscle-making gene.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.43,1:36:14.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,为何会有区别呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why was there such a difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.33,1:36:18.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,为何这种基因使得一种物种能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What did this gene enable one species to do
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.30,1:36:21.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,做其他物种所不能的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the other could not?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.27,1:36:25.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼 开始研究类人猿中这一基因所扮演的角色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stedman began to research the role of this gene in apes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.41,1:36:30.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,他发现这一基因构成了一种特殊肌肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he found it made one particular kind of muscle--
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.41,1:36:33.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,咀嚼肌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the muscle for chewing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.32,1:36:37.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 这种肌肉用来合拢下巴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact,the muscle used to close the jaw.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.29,1:36:42.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,对人类来说 这种基因遗传意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In humans,that genetic glitch meant that we chew
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.36,1:36:46.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,跟类人猿相比 我们只是用一小部分力量来咀嚼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with just a fraction of the force of an ape.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.30,1:36:49.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,这本身很有趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This in itself was interesting,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.50,1:36:53.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而斯特德曼接下来研究的才真有趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but where Stedman went next was truly intriguing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.24,1:36:57.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时 也极具争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and highly controversial.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.31,1:36:59.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,他把我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He drew a direct connection
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.44,1:37:02.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,下颌肌肉的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the power of our jaw muscle
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.38,1:37:06.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,和人类大脑的进化直接联系起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the evolution of the human brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.42,1:37:17.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼是这么想的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stedman's thinking goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.26,1:37:19.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,类人猿和人类的头骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The skulls of apes and humans
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.46,1:37:23.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,是由几块独立的骨板组成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are made of several independent bone plates.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.50,1:37:27.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些骨板使得我们的头随着发育逐渐长大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They let our heads get bigger as we grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.51,1:37:33.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,而用于咀嚼的肌肉拉扯着这些骨板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The muscles for chewing pull against these plates.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.48,1:37:38.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,这力量可是巨大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in an ape,these forces can be enormous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.45,1:37:43.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼：在大猩猩中 这块肌肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}STEDMAN: In the gorilla,the muscle-
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.29,1:37:45.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,有人类大腿肌肉那么大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the size of a human thigh muscle--
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.42,1:37:49.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,长在这儿 并且得穿过这么大的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lives here and has to go through this large space
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.26,1:37:52.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,来使下颌前后移动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to power the jaw moving back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.36,1:37:55.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们并不是在谈论二头肌 也不是三头肌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're not talking biceps,tricep,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.30,1:37:56.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,而是四头肌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're talking quad here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.43,1:37:58.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可是块大肌肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is an enormous muscle
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.37,1:38:01.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,它得穿过这个洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has to come right through this hole here
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.37,1:38:05.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,来启动关闭下颌装置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to power the jaw-closing apparatus.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.31,1:38:10.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼 认为 在初期 这些所有的肌肉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Stedman contends that all this muscle power
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.48,1:38:14.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,都迫使类人猿的颅骨板融合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forces an ape's skull plates to fuse together at an early stage,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.35,1:38:21.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这也限制了大脑可以长到多大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this puts limits on how much the brain can grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.52,1:38:25.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼：在黑猩猩 大猩猩或者猩猩中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}STEDMAN: In a chimpanzee,gorilla,orangutan,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.40,1:38:29.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,在他们大约三到四岁时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those growth plates are pretty much shut down,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.43,1:38:32.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些骨板几乎都停止了生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}closed for business by about three,four years of age.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.60,1:38:36.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,而人类中 他们却能长到30岁左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a human,they remain open for growth to perhaps age 30.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.55,1:38:47.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,斯特德曼认为 这 就是关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: This,Stedman believes,is the key.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.48,1:38:51.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,下颌肌肉的突变 使得人类头骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A mutation in our jaw muscle allows the human skull
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.39,1:38:55.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,不断发育至成年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to keep expanding into adulthood,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.39,1:38:59.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们的大脑也有了更大的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating a bigger space for our brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.60,1:39:06.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此我们人类最重要的器官就能发育成长了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so our most important organ is able to grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.47,1:39:14.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,某种肌肉改变的突变可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's very cool to us to think that some kind
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.38,1:39:18.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,会是人类成为独特物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of muscle-altering mutation might have actually been
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.61,1:39:22.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,的标志性事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a signature event in the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.59,1:39:27.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,这想想就很让人激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what makes us distinct as a species.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.59,1:39:31.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,这很可能是我们之所以成为我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It might have been an absolute prerequisite
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.59,1:39:35.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,的绝对先决条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for us landing where we are today.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.60,1:39:43.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,然而 有了一个可以容纳大脑的空间是一回事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: But having the space for a big brain is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.51,1:39:48.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,而要想长出大脑需要什么又是另一回事了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is needed to actually grow one?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.52,1:39:58.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,这正是 克里斯 沃尔什 试图回答的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is the question that Chris Walsh is trying to answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.42,1:40:01.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,他是未科学家 可从没想过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he's another scientist who never expected
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.66,1:40:04.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,他将从事连达尔文都不明白的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be taking on what even Darwin didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.43,1:40:07.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,沃尔什：我从未想过我将研究进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WALSH: I never thought that I'd be studying evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.43,1:40:08.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是一名神经学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm a neurologist
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.36,1:40:12.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,对研究大脑和和患有神经问题的儿童很感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}interested in the brain and kids with neurological broblems.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.54,1:40:16.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好 伙计 还好吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How you doing,buddy? Are you doing all right,huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.51,1:40:17.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You doing okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.64,1:40:19.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,当发现研究这些残疾儿童\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one was more surprised than us
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.54,1:40:23.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,会涉及到那些迷人的进化史问题时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to find that the study of kids with disabilities would lead us
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.55,1:40:26.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想没人比我们吃惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into these fascinating evolutionary questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.38,1:40:29.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,他白天呼吸还好么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is his breathing generally okay during the day?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.49,1:40:32.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,当他收到惊吓的时候 会比较快就像...\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes when he gets started,it will go up fast,like...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.62,1:40:33.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,喘气声\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}(panting)
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.49,1:40:36.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,但当他冷静下来的时候 就不会了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...but then he calms himself right back down...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.59,1:40:40.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,沃尔什 是 一种罕见疾病---头小畸形 方面的专家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: Walsh is a specialist in a rare disorder called microcephaly.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.40,1:40:45.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,头小畸形患儿生下来时头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Children with microcephaly are born with brains
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.54,1:40:48.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,就只有正常的一半大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can be half the normal size.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.57,1:40:50.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,沃尔什：这种疾病对患儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WALSH: This disorder can be very devastating
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.61,1:40:51.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,危害极大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the kids that have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.64,1:40:54.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们通常智力迟钝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They typically will have severe mental retardation,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.64,1:40:57.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此无法正常的语言习得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so will not be able to achieve normal language
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.61,1:40:58.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,和接受教育\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and normal schooling.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.65,1:41:02.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种事情制约着整个家庭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so it's really an event that defines the whole family.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.55,1:41:05.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是患儿本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It defines the lives not only of the child,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.45,1:41:06.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有患儿的父母亲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but of the parents of that child.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.56,1:41:09.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,这些家庭都迫切希望\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these families are desperately eager
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.73,1:41:13.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,至少了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to try to understand at least
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.43,1:41:14.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,到底是什么引起了这种疾病\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what caused the disorder in their kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.70,1:41:18.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,沃尔什 这项工作最初的目的在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: The purpose of Walsh's work
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.43,1:41:21.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,帮助那些可能携带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was initially to help families that might be carrying
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.70,1:41:25.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,任何导致头小畸形病的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any defective genes causing microcephaly
