Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.03,1:47:25.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,可以称之为基因开关的DNA序列上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we can think of as switches--
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.94,1:47:29.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们是一些能够开启或关闭附近基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're pieces of DNA that turn a nearby gene on or off...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.01,1:47:34.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,告诉它们何时在我们身体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that tell it where,in what cells in our body,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.01,1:47:37.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪个组织哪个细胞的何处达到什么程度时运行的DNA片段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in what tissue,at what time or at what level to be operating.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.92,1:47:42.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,关于这些基因开关 还有些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And there was something even more intriguing
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.92,1:47:44.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,更有趣的事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about those switches.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.92,1:47:46.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,大量的 估计有一半以上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A large number of them,more than half,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.82,1:47:50.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,的DNA片段就在跟大脑有关的基因附近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were nearby a gene that was involved in the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.90,1:47:55.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,在波拉德的工作中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: In Pollard's work,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.03,1:47:58.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,一个特殊的DNA片段很显著\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one particular piece of DNA stood out.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.87,1:48:03.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,这种DNA序列在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a piece of DNA that is known to be active
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.04,1:48:07.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,胚胎的大脑关键部位发育时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the development of one of the key parts of the human brain
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.84,1:48:09.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,变得非常活跃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the embryo...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.85,1:48:11.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是大脑皮质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.98,1:48:15.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,大脑皮质就是我们大脑外面那皱皱的一层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cortex is that wrinkled outer layer of our brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.02,1:48:21.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,它对人类的语言能力 学习音乐和数学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's vital for those defining human capabilities
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.82,1:48:25.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,至关重要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like language,music and mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.90,1:48:36.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,当她把黑猩猩和鸡中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When she looked at that DNA in chimps
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.11,1:48:39.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,相同DNA序列对比时发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and compared it to the same DNA in a chicken,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.14,1:48:43.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,仅有两处碱基不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was different in just two letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.01,1:48:47.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,而这与人类却存在着18处不同的碱基\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in humans it was different by 18 letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.09,1:48:54.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这可是巨大的突变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A massive mutation.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.96,1:48:59.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,作为科学家，这可绝对是个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was about as great of a eureka moment as you could have
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.13,1:49:01.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,“尤里卡”时刻 （阿基米德洗澡时若有所思地叫了一声“尤里卡” 从此发现了阿基米德定律）\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.90,1:49:05.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,这又是个有趣的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: So here is another intriguing piece of evidence
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.07,1:49:09.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,它告诉我们DNA是如何塑造人类独有特征的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suggesting how DNA can shape our distinctive human qualities.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.14,1:49:14.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在，我们知道了DNA的许多不同工作方式，\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We now know that DNA works in many different ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.14,1:49:18.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如通过基因来构造我们的躯体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through genes that make the stuff of our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.08,1:49:22.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,通过基因开关来开启或关闭基因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through switches that turn those genes on and off
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.05,1:49:25.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及通过DNA序列上的碱基\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and through sequences of DNA's chemicals
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.92,1:49:27.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,来启动这些基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that throw those switches.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.92,1:49:30.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,把这一切都串联起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Taken together,what this all adds up to
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.13,1:49:32.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们最终会发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a way that we can at last understand
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.96,1:49:36.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,DNA只要一个小小的改变，就能产生巨大的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how small differences in DNA can generate enormous change.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.97,1:49:42.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,波拉德：基本上 只要改变这些基因开关\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}POLLARD: Basically,you can make massive changes
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.11,1:49:44.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,就能产生巨大的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just changing those switches.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.07,1:49:47.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 一个小小的变化 几个DNA碱基\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So a small change,a couple of DNA letters,could have
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.94,1:49:51.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,也能产生深刻地影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.18,1:49:55.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,因此 达尔文的终极谜题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: And so that final Darwinian puzzle--
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.05,1:49:58.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,人类是如何和类人猿紧密相关却又如此不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how a human can be so closely related to an ape
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.95,1:50:02.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,正在逐步地获得解答\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and yet be so different-- is now slowly being answered.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.97,1:50:14.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,自达尔文提出他的理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}150 years after Darwin first put forward his grand theory
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.97,1:50:20.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,以解释生物的多样性 经过150年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to explain the great diversity of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.08,1:50:25.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,科学家们秉承着他留下的遗产\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the scientists who carry on his legacy have advanced his work
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.08,1:50:29.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,以各种奇妙的方法延续着他的研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in wondrous ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.15,1:50:31.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,我认为 如果达尔文今日依然活着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think if Darwin were here today,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.99,1:50:33.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,他绝对会震惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he'd be absolutely stunned,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.22,1:50:37.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,高兴甚至会感动地发现他的理论已经被如此地发扬光大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}delighted,even moved to see how much his theory has grown.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.26,1:50:43.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,塔宾：我们现在所能解释的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}TABIN: What we now are able to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.03,1:50:45.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,一方面可能会把他吓跑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the one hand would just blow him away.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.17,1:50:47.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,但另一方面我觉得他将会非常满意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But I also think it would give him enormous satisfaction,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.24,1:50:51.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们正研究的一切都验证了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because ultimately everything we've been learing validates
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.24,1:50:54.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,他的想法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the things that he said.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.01,1:50:56.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,贾德森：我觉得达尔文市委非常了不起的科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}JUDSON: I think that Darwin was a ramarkable scientist
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.25,1:50:58.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,绝对称得上非常出色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and absolutely should be celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.15,1:51:02.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是 我并不认为他会是进化论的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However,I do not think that he was the end of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.09,1:51:04.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,相反 我认为他只是给我们开了个头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the contrary,I think he was the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.29,1:51:08.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,他给我们概述了重点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He outlined the major points,but we have discovered more
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.19,1:51:12.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,而我们的发现已经远远超过了他的所想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than I think he would have imagined possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.16,1:51:18.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,当我们庆祝查尔斯 达尔文200岁生日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NARRATOR: As we celebrate the 200th birthday of Charles Darwin
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.00,1:51:22.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及他的伟大理论诞辰150周年的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the 150th anniversary of his great work,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.17,1:51:26.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,关于大自然无穷无尽的演化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is still much more to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.01,1:51:29.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,依然还有许许多多地方需要我们探究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about how the endless forms of nature have arisen.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.22,1:51:42.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,同时 为了应付这一挑战\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in rising to that challenge,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.02,1:51:45.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们将继续推进医药发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is likely that we will continue to advance medicine
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.16,1:51:48.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,以便更好地了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and come to a better understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.06,1:51:52.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们人类本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of ourselves as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.01,1:52:00.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,NOVA 的全新“进化”网已经上线了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NOVA has a brand-new Evolution Web site
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.18,1:52:03.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,视频 采访 幻灯片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with dozens of videos,interviews,slide shows
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.18,1:52:05.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,以及进化科学上的最新发现等 应有尽有\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the latest in evolutionary science.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.18,1:52:08.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,请添加书签 让我们获知你们所想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bookmark it today and let us know what you think.
